∫¯áL∏Àå’4nË m3{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "07c29b9f-241b-4ef2-8c17-264a694ca162", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:31.145286", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "117ea57f5017f5edc66beabbe009f261187c3137eb8f81ecb032ad45df861205"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "author": "JohnDeSando", "rating": null, "date": "2026-02-06", "title": null, "content": "I'll confirm that I enjoy a B movie with the rest of the world. In fact, after reviewing the Likes of Hamnet and Sentimental Value, to name only 2 heavy duty recent cinemas, I relax most with Jason Statham's frolics, recently Shelter. By ramping up the emotional level, he elevates the screenplay while still easily dispatching several opponents.\n\nMichael Mason (Statham), hiding out on a Scottish island, rescues a young girl, Jessie (Bodhi Rae Breathnach) from a storm but reveals his true assassin identity to authorities when he has to go ashore to get medicine for her broken ankle. Most of the story involves protecting her and himself from corrupt MI6 operatives and lavishing love on his dog, Jack, and, not surprisingly, Jessie herself.\n\nShe is an outstanding actress while Jason is more taciturn than Charles Bronson but displaying more inner emotion like love than Charlie ever dredged up except for the children in The Magnificent Seven. Here Mason seems sincerely to love Jessie and is willing to die for her if necessary.\n\nThe UK is lovingly photographed and minor characters like Bill Nighy's bad boy Manafort are well cast. But the dog and the girl are to die for, yet that's not possible because Statham knows his B movies with many more, I hope, to come. Shelter is plain good thriller with an unusual measure of emotion-it's what movies do."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "511eed03-9ed2-497c-895f-5e2fd2a69b3e", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:31.145286", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "bdd2fc15164aa514504c36e66bdc23553eb2c318287e78b9b3c5be3b5c84f760"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "author": "AK1991", "rating": 7, "date": "2026-01-31", "title": null, "content": "As a fan of Jason Statham's style of action films, Shelter met my expectations. It delivers grounded, old-school action with no flashy CGI-just solid fight scenes, practical stunt work, and some brutal bad-guy deaths. Statham brings his usual gruff, charismatic, and likable screen presence, and the cool locations help keep things visually engaging. It's also a movie that works well on the big screen, making it a solid cinema watch.\n\nWhile the story is familiar and occasionally slow-burning, it carries more emotion and character drama than some of his more action-heavy films, such as A Working Man. That added weight makes it easier to invest in the story and gives the final stretch a stronger payoff when the action kicks in.\n\nThis isn't a top-tier Statham classic, but it's a strong mid-tier entry in his action filmography-one I could easily revisit and enjoy again. Recommended for Statham fans and lovers of old-school action.\n\nRating: 7/10."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "138bd18b-4ecd-470c-b8c0-9d0ac84f5579", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:31.145286", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "d59892e58acda4fadbd5332a4530145bad04b45e8927c6149a1ddd36d1b29c74"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "author": "nERDbOX_Dave", "rating": 6, "date": "2026-02-01", "title": null, "content": "There's a moment you hit in life when you realize you've become your parents. For me, it happened while watching Shelter. As a kid, I never understood why my dad was glued to Steven Seagal and Jean-Claude Van Damme movies and yet here I am, still showing up for Jason Statham. Time is a flat circle, apparently.\n\nShelter finds Statham once again playing a man running from a shadowy past. This time, he's Michael Mason, a former government assassin living in self-imposed exile on a remote coastal island. No fake job this time, no construction worker, no beekeeper, no armored car driver. We've officially run out of cover occupations. Instead, Mason is just there, hiding from the world and hoping the world forgets him.\n\nThat peace is shattered when he rescues a young girl, Jessie (Bodhi Rae Breathnach), from a violent storm. After a tragic accident leaves her orphaned, Mason is forced into an uneasy guardianship that slowly turns into something resembling a family. Predictably, his past refuses to stay buried. A trip into town puts him back on MI6's radar, and soon Mason and Jessie are on the run, hunted by government elites, a rogue covert ops unit, and the ghosts of Mason's former life.\n\nTo the film's credit, Shelter shines brightest in its opening act. Before Mason flips the switch into full combat mode, there's genuine drama here. Statham is restrained, quiet, and effective when the film allows him to be something other than a delivery system for punches and one-liners. His scenes with Breathnach feel sincere, and for a brief stretch, Shelter hints at being something more character-driven.\n\nThis is the Jason Statham I want more of. Someone please call Guy Ritchie and remind him that Statham doesn't always need to throw a punch to be compelling. Put him back in a gritty crime drama. Let him act.\n\nUnfortunately, once the chase begins, Shelter falls back into familiar territory. The film pairs Statham with yet another young female sidekick he must protect, echoing Safe. Bill Nighy brings some gravitas as Manafort, Mason's former handler, while Naomi Ackie and Daniel Mays do solid work with what they're given, but none of it is enough to elevate the material.\n\nFrom there, it becomes the usual Statham routine. Like a slasher movie, you start wondering less if he'll kill someone and more how creatively he'll do it this time. The problem is... nothing really stands out. The action is competent but forgettable, and no set piece truly jumps off the screen.\n\nAfter last year's The Working Man, a film that nearly broke my Statham loyalty, Shelter is at least a step up. It's better. It's more watchable. But it's also painfully middle-of-the-road. The story is decent enough to throw on at home, but there's nothing here screaming \"must-see on the big screen.\""}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "d863f476-977d-495f-b8f2-9f81b6873458", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:31.145286", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "42e7418bf1673c5093c7c1a9531ecfd273af16448d3c6385853a29bdc2b32db4"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "author": "masonsaul", "rating": 6, "date": "2026-01-31", "title": null, "content": "Shelter is a standard issue Jason Statham action vehicle that offers nothing new and tells a very generic story borrowed from better movies; however it manages to deliver the necessary goods for one of these serviceable films which often operate as entertaining if disposable cinema. There's enough action interspersed throughout despite a slow start and a 107 minute run time that feels slightly too long with a decent amount of heart in its central dynamic to plug the gaps.\n\nJason Statham continues to be a formidable leading man who once again avoids phoning it in even if he's playing the same character because the film would be dead on arrival if he did. He's the main reason any of this works and his unwavering commitment is a bit more vital than usual since supporting players Daniel Mays, Naomi Ackie and Bill Nighy are barely given anything to do. Bodhi Rae Breathnach fares a lot better thanks to her believable bond with Statham.\n\nRic Roman Waugh's workmanlike direction gets the job done and improves as it goes along. Martin Ahlgren's cinematography can get a little hard to follow in some of the action scenes but is still able to deliver a couple of really solid hand to hand fights and an intense car chase. Composer David Buckley is an ideal choice for this because of his previous collaborations with Waugh and the fact that he's done a Bourne film previously so his score always matches the film's look and feel."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "3fb1100b-8a3a-4bce-a0c0-2318f81a6a2a", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:31.145286", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "9952d5c5490e9da6ce6d90819e218ae702d04a7fffaf7a6e9c3f8dea95a9b82b"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "author": "vengeance20", "rating": 8, "date": "2026-01-30", "title": null, "content": "So, I saw a trailer for this & being a Jason Statham fan, I knew I had to go & watch it.\n\nA recluse on a remote Scottish island rescues a girl from the sea, unleashing a perilous sequence of events that culminate in an attack on his home, compelling him to face his turbulent history.\n\nI found the film to be pretty good. It was slow to start I will say, but once the bullets & sparks start to fly, boy does it get going & doesn't let up from there either as it's non-stop action. The story is a bit muddled & half baked, but, it's not bad & you pretty much get it anyway.\n\nThe cast including the main man himself do a good job. Jason never disappoints with his films even if they're ok & not amazing. The action is pretty good & the film brisks along at a steady pace despite the slow start. At 1 hour & 41 minutes (101 minutes), it's decently lengthed.\n\nThe film ends on a good note & of course Statham does the job well he produced this film as well as acted in it. It's not one of his best films, but it's a decent Statham flick with plenty of action, fights & gun battles so it doesn't disappoint at all.\n\nOverall, it's a pretty solid flick. It's not amazing, but it's pretty good & one you should definitely check out if you haven't already.\n\n8/10."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "961c8fc7-91cc-41ad-be0b-d87ee69aac41", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:31.145286", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "e45b95e00b3d0c252ba37a132d11f83cb019a578f5fa2a2b998378d378148cf5"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "author": "Hakihiko", "rating": 6, "date": "2026-02-25", "title": null, "content": "\"Shelter\" is very much what you expect from a Jason Statham vehicle: straightforward, action-driven, and built around his tough, no-nonsense screen presence. It doesn't try to reinvent the genre, but it knows its lane and stays firmly within it.\n\nThe plot is fairly standard, moving from one confrontation to the next with a predictable structure. There aren't many surprises along the way, and the script doesn't aim for much depth. Still, the pacing keeps things watchable, and the film rarely feels boring.\n\nStatham delivers exactly what he's known for: controlled intensity, physical credibility, and that familiar stoic charisma. It's not a performance that stretches his range, but it doesn't need to. The action sequences are solid and competently staged, providing enough impact to satisfy fans of the genre.\n\nIn the end, \"Shelter\" is classic Statham entertainment. Nothing groundbreaking, nothing particularly memorable, but reliably enjoyable for what it is."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "589ed2f2-46be-42e3-b31c-73e441d3b600", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:31.145286", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "7d24c11d3cc563d1ef115a6248aa788b4edf136b1d55f79cf9dab3b262bbe2c8"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "author": "Billy_Boy_", "rating": 7, "date": "2026-02-02", "title": null, "content": "Two things about this movie:\n\nWhat didn't surprise me is that Shelter is exactly what you'd expect from a Jason Statham film: A straightforward, no-nonsense action movie where he shows up, takes a beating, gives out even worse ones and walks away like nothing ever touched him at the end.\n\nWhat surprised me though is how much I actually liked Shelter: The action is actually very solid, the pacing is good once it gets going and the plot, while predictable, was pretty fun as well."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "e9b4818f-7c5d-400d-885e-6fae7a940e3c", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:31.145286", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "6eb995c89765829a6b7b9f70d86c0b7e2c860ad2dd7511b84ff327ab1afb656e"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "author": "slightlymad22", "rating": 7, "date": "2026-02-02", "title": null, "content": "I have just got out of Jason Statham's new movie Shelter.\n\nIf you have seen one Jason Statham solo movie, you have seen them all. But there is a lot of fun to be had with them, at least, the good ones.\n\nAnd I enjoyed this, it has a bit of heart to it. Statham does what Statham does, but it was his young costar (Bodhi Rae Breathnach) who elevated this to the next level, for me. She was great. I think this was my first time seeing her, but I think she could have a great career.\n\nBill Nighy collects possibly his easiest paycheck ever, as he is not given a lot to do. The cast are all competent performers, though, so no complaints there.\n\nI only have two complaints.... This doesn't feel like a 15 rated (in the UK) movie. It's 12A (or PG13) for sure. Lots of people die, but it's not explicit in any way. I also thought the movie was going to go in a certain direction, with lots of foreshadowing, but it didn't follow through with it.\n\nAll in all, a routine and predictable Jason Statham movie, that I had a good time with."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "fb631cca-8d19-424c-9a0c-91d4176f7d45", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:31.145286", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "bd86c438452b21cb2b72c81f2f08750d79a788cb04f576c211f5a542f7c99ba5"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "author": "davidhock", "rating": 6, "date": "2026-02-14", "title": null, "content": "We have a specific cultural contract with Jason Statham. He provides the brawling, we provide the popcorn, and nobody asks for a receipt. Shelter is the ultimate expression of this deal a movie that manages to be perfectly entertaining while being entirely invisible.\n\nThe film relies on the simple, primal joy of watching someone who is very good at what they do. The setup is a classic archetype: take a reclusive ex-marine, put him in a lighthouse, and hand him a vulnerable girl to save. It isn't about the \"why\" or the \"how\"; it's about the reassurance of a protagonist who knows exactly where the flare gun is kept when the storm hits. He's a one-man wrecking ball with a compass, and watching him work is the main event.\n\nThe Verdict You won't see this on any Oscar ballots, but you won't regret the ticket price either. Shelter is a solid entry in the mid-tier action genre. It hits every beat of the \"reluctant savior\" formula with surgical precision, leaving you satisfied but with absolutely nothing to discuss the next morning. It's a solid Friday night win that stays exactly where it belongs: in the theater."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "1353f2cc-d899-4070-bbbf-9ba893d2f732", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:31.145286", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "2495d63975c2e68237c820405a2cd7a99b37f6d744029083b110eac9533bddcd"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "author": "theromanempire-1", "rating": 9, "date": "2026-02-10", "title": null, "content": "This was another solid action thriller film starring jason statham.\n\nThis time we get a more depressed atmosphere in first 20 minutes showing a loner statham hiding in an abandoned small island pretending to be a lighthouse keeper until he is forced to save a little grl from certain death when strong winds nearly drowned the girl and from there the action is a go.\n\nIf u love statham u must see this film in a theater and then get the dvd for your collection."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "904d2ee0-be74-4082-902c-d913a515163e", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:31.145286", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "455ad04f2d0b6cdf603158bf38c34082d519a86c9ff24efe937993aec774de65"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "author": "saolivaresm", "rating": 6, "date": "2026-02-28", "title": null, "content": "Ric Roman Waugh delivers a solid action thriller in its development, presenting us with a more cautious and emotional Jason Statham within a well-executed proposal.\n\nOn a remote island, a man living in exile (Jason Statham) saves a young girl from a dangerous storm, setting off a chain of events that puts them both in grave danger. As their paths cross, his goal becomes protecting her at all costs, while he confronts enemies from his past in an intense and thrilling fight for survival.\n\nThis film delivers on its promise. With solid direction and committed performances from its leads, it offers an action thriller with intense moments of both tension and staging. It makes good use of its budget to provide an experience that, while not groundbreaking, evokes the classics of the genre.\n\nIt's another perfect excuse to sit back and get pumped up watching Statham throw punches. What's wrong with that? Absolutely nothing, since Statham gives it his all, and although it's a film in the actor's signature style, he manages to add nuance and layers to a character and a relationship that, at times, recalls the classic *The Professional* starring Jean Reno and Natalie Portman. It doesn't reach the heights of that film, but it does evoke similar feelings.\n\nIts soundtrack is incredible and perhaps the most stimulating aspect of the film. David Buckley blends instrumental music with techno touches that add tension and excitement to the viewing experience, while Martin Ahlgren achieves magnificent cinematography of the UK landscapes.\n\nWith the delightful surprise of Bodhi Rae Breathnach as our protagonist's loyal sidekick, we find an action thriller that delivers solid entertainment. It offers what it promises, with intensity and justified drama, without losing sight of providing a story that not only features fights and chases, but also a close relationship between two damaged souls who come together to give themselves a second chance."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "f75f31ed-d551-4d8f-a3a7-7fe0baf9558f", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:31.145286", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "860dfe8b2e2f8cc50d2e0f501e56d9839f8ca63b98b3e400a68cf1294670f264"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "author": "darkreignn", "rating": 8, "date": "2026-02-01", "title": null, "content": "\"Shelter\" caught me off guard in the best way. Jason Statham movies usually deliver exactly what you want from them with brutal action and thrilling set pieces - but \"Shelter\" leans much more into drama and heart than you'd expect, and I absolutely loved it for that. Directed by Ric Roman Waugh, the film follows a recluse named Mason who lives alone on a remote Scottish island. When a massive storm strands a young girl named Jesse (played by Bodhi Rae Breathnach) after her uncle's boat capsizes, Mason rescues her, and what starts as reluctant protection turns into this genuine, emotional bond that really carries the movie and makes it unlike any Statham action movie in recent memory.\n\nIf you're going to see this, you're most likely going for Statham's trademarked action style, so have no fear - the action here is really good and exciting, with satisfying fights, car chases, and shootouts that hit hard. Waugh's action style keeps things slightly shaky and handheld to amp up the intensity, like a faux-documentary where the camera feels present without turning into seizure-shaky nonsense. You can always see what's happening clearly, so the punches land, the chases feel visceral, and the shootouts have real weight. So, if you're going in purely for action, you'll get plenty of that payoff, but it's not the nonstop explosion-fest some Statham films are, so just know that before buying a ticket.\n\nFor me, what made \"Shelter\" really stand out - and what I really want to emphasize - is the relationship between Jason Statham and Bodhi Rae Breathnach. Their bond is the heart of the film, and it's surprisingly emotional and heartwarming to watch. Statham dials it way back here for a quieter, more dramatic performance showing real restraint and vulnerability in small ways that feel earned. Bodhi Rae Breathnach is fantastic as Jesse, and the way these two guarded people slowly open up to each other through quiet conversations, shared survival moments, and little gestures, is genuinely moving. It's not sappy; it's real and touching, and it gives the action stakes beyond just \"kill the bad guys.\" Also, Statham and Bodhi just have excellent chemistry, and I honestly found myself getting teary eyed at points because of how beautiful their relationship was.\n\nI loved this movie more than I expected because, while the action delivers the thrills, the dramatic core and that father-figure dynamic between Mason and Jesse make it feel like more than just another Statham vehicle. It's a solid mix of tense set pieces and heartfelt character work, and Statham's quieter side shines in a way we don't always get to see. If you're looking for pure action, it's there and it's good; but stick around for the emotional payoff - it's what elevates the whole thing and makes it worth watching. I'll definitely rewatch this one for those bonding scenes and Statham's understated performance. Solid January surprise."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "1a0535f5-22b2-4175-b687-346861914736", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:31.145286", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "2631f32af9585539d242b2747ec409d1edeb4c1d7e4dde72b4c897b1891641bd"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "author": "UrbonasG", "rating": 7, "date": "2026-01-29", "title": null, "content": "I came not expecting much, my expectations were not exceeded but I had a great time nonetheless.\n\nIt's your generic Jason Stathom movie. He comes in, beats the crap out of everybody, and then calmly leaves. The action, the fighting, it's all there, and it's great. Hell, it should be the entire reason you're buying tickets for this. Get some snacks and drinks, turn your brain off, and enjoy."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "a51c4443-aaa1-4696-8e6c-0543f9b43801", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:31.145286", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "2658c9013d83cd3c26ae8dad651df4735f693164f57d52c60c70bedf40e87b62"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "author": "kuner-59029", "rating": 5, "date": "2026-02-02", "title": null, "content": "Jason Statham has kind of become the Charles Bronson of our age. His movies are mostly twists on the same formula. Retired secret agent killer lives in seclusion doing an odd job (okay, this time he's not even employed, but he lives in a light house). Bad guys show up and force him out of retirement. Unlike the Beekeeper or Working man, they decided to give him a child sidekick this time. Someone to care about and have dialogue with instead of just having him show up like a Michael Myers with guns to murder people for 100 minutes. They did the same thing with \"Safe\" before.\n\nOn paper, this is a foolproof idea. But somehow, even in the age of ChatGPT, they managed to screw up this concept. It's not the director's fault. The film is competently directed, far better than The Beekeeper or Safe.\n\nBut the script has 2 fatal flaws it can't overcome. While it starts out incredibly strong with the storm scene, the film falls apart with its villains. There barely are any. Statham has to fight soldiers and cops. So when he brutally maims and murders them, the viewer don't get the psychological satisfaction of seeing bad guys die. These are just working shlubs trying to make ends meet. Halfway through the film they must have realized this, and Statham doesn't kill the cops.\n\nThere is one main heavy of course, the usual highly trained assassin, and the scenes with him are tense and perfectly choreographed as one would expect. We never get a sense of who that guy is though. He doesn't even speak to Statham.\n\nThe main baddie, introduced early in the movie, is a wet noodle of a character. Boring every time he is on screen and only ever wearing one facial expression.\n\nInstead, we get pointless scenes with strong diverse female MI6 woman who with her team of strong independent MI6 women eventually catches on that Statham is a good guy who was framed. So him killing scores of MI6 agents is acceptable then.\n\nThe relationship between Statham and the girl at the heart of the film is poorly written. I can't fault the actors, the script gives them nearly nothing to work with. Statham shows virtually no emotion at all, and the girl doesn't either. Even early on she doesn't scream, doesn't cry, doesn't panic. She just argues with Statham. Later on in the film she becomes so unemotional that she literally says \"maybe i'm becoming like you.\"\n\nWhoever write the dialogue in this film: Use AI next time.\n\nCredit to the director and main cast for somehow still keeping the film afloat. The brisk pace and incredibly well choreographed action scenes are engaging and Statham is fun to watch, somehow even more so as he gets older and more gruff. Just like Charles Bronson.\n\nWith a bit of polish and a better script, this could have been a solid 8/10 or even higher. What a missed opportunity."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "d5d5e0b2-09d4-4353-9be3-7979222373f9", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:31.145286", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "f7748b0bbc4576c4a38f8aa64c57d1bcdd26a134a1aa2380b5c15336f4912a9c"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "author": "jared-25331", "rating": 9, "date": "2026-02-03", "title": null, "content": "Shelter (2026) is an action thriller movie directed by Ric Roman Waugh and it follows a man living in self-imposed exile on a remote island who rescues a young girl from a violent storm, which sets off a chain of events that forces him out of seclusion to protect her from enemies tied to his past. This is a movie that I was really looking forward to watching since I am a massive fan of Jason Statham and Ric Roman Waugh and I wanted to see some fun action and that is exactly what I got from this movie.\n\nPositives for Shelter (2026): The story is good enough for your typical action thriller movie and it worked for me. I get a lot of fun from these Jason Statham movies as he is one of those actors who knows what his fans want from him. Jason Statham does a great job as the main character of Michael Mason as he gets to kick all of the asses of the bad guys. I also liked Bodhi Rae Breathnach as Jessie, who manages to bring the emotion needed for the story and her dynamic with Statham was great. The supporting cast is great for what they had to work with. The action sequences are good enough for this movie. And finally, this is one of those good old fashion hangout movies that you can enjoy with some friends and good food.\n\nMixed for Shelter (2026): This movie is exactly what you would expect from Jason Statham, whose are in their own subgenre like Liam Neeson and not all of them are going to work for everyone.\n\nNegatives for Shelter (2026): While the action sequences were fun, they're not on the same level of awesomeness I've seen in other Jason Statham movies like The Beekeeper (2023) and that was a bit of a disappointment for me.\n\nOverall, Shelter (2026) is exactly what you get from a Jason Statham movie and I had fun with it even if it isn't among his instant classics from the past."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "e0951c4e-036d-4ac4-af48-c1690081b9b2", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:31.145286", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "6a4248aaf77a1d94eee769ee7f59f5c78a363667e8ea5ce300a8c9eff4f54bd1"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "author": "DoNotComeToTheCinemaDepressed", "rating": 8, "date": "2026-01-30", "title": null, "content": "Just Got Out of a Dolby Cinema Screening of Shelter.\n\nLook At this Point, You Should Know What You Are Going to Get in a Jason Statham Film. Jason Statham Films are Like Coke, Cherry Coke, Diet Coke, Coke Lime, Coke Vanilla, Coke Lemon, Coke Zero, Coke Blueberry. At Some Point, there's Only So Much You Can Do.\n\nWhat I liked About the Film -\n\n\ud83c\udf1f - Jason Statham puts in a Good Performance Here, From the Action Scenes to the Acting, he plays this Sorrowful, World-weary Outcast. It's Good.\n\n\ud83c\udf1f - Bodhi Rae Breathnach as Jessie, She's Spirited and She's Solid in the Role. She could have a Bright Future Ahead of Her in Film.\n\n\ud83c\udfb5 - The Score was really Good, the Gloomy Parts of the Score particularly at the start when they are on the island. And the Thumping Electric Score \u26a1 during certain Scenes.\n\n\ud83d\udca3 - The Action Scenes are Solid, the Hand To Hand (and Kicks) Fights are Good to Watch.\n\n\ud83d\udc83 - I Really Liked the Club Scene, The Thumping Club Music and Action was Again, Good To Watch.\n\n\ud83d\udcc3 - Other Performances, Bill Nighy and Naomi Ackie are Competent Performances with What they Are Given to do.\n\nGripes with the Film -\n\n\ud83d\udcc3 - The Storyline in that 2nd and 3rd act(1st Act on the Island was Great), definitely left a lot to be desired.\n\n\ud83e\udd26 - The Generic Bad Guy that they send after Statham, he's a nothing Character, and that doesn't add anything to the film, there's no Heat Between Him and Statham, Barely any Verbal Interaction between the two, and it definitely dampens the film.\n\nBut Overall, it was A Good Watch."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "0dd794a3-fc8f-44b9-ad5f-24f4bedd1aed", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:31.145286", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "3b0c8d6e4282d9b99bc8d06bca4f673a8fcd6d20cd4146e47ca91a23f17e4294"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "author": "FiftyTwo_52", "rating": 6, "date": "2026-03-03", "title": null, "content": "A typical Statham movie - fairly standard, not bad but not one of his better efforts.\n\nThe main problem is pacing: it takes a full 45 min to set up the main story, which really only kicks in at the farmhouse scene (which is great). Worse, that first 45 minutes had ample time but completely failed to establish the bond between Statham and the girl, which should be the backbone of the entire emotional thread. When the film asks you to care about their relationship, you realize it never earned that investment.\n\nOnce the action starts, it delivers: good fight choreography, some clever twists, and solid entertainment without being pretentious. Statham does what Statham does reliably. Bodhi Rae Breathnach makes a genuine impression in her limited role... she's got charisma and screen presence that elevate her scenes.\n\n6/10: It's watchable and professionally made, but ultimately forgettable. A decent Friday night watch, nothing more."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "6cc11e1f-9d1a-4fb6-8f4f-87fb5b42b9fc", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:31.145286", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "84f115c1dd2e5aef438b34e67b8396bd2727e903f89d0fdee25dc5978037fb5d"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "author": "bettillee", "rating": 10, "date": "2026-02-01", "title": null, "content": "This movie is typical Jason Statham fare, but that's a perk. I don't care what he's in, whether it's considered a good or a bad movie, he always delivers the action for me. This movie is standard Statham as I said, but it's actually a bit more exciting than some of his older movies. He's more world weary, grizzled and worn, but it just adds to his appeal and he still looks and acts great. You absolutely can't fall asleep on this one, and there's a lot of it that's just plain fun. The premise is a good one, and the little girl lives up to all the hype. This movie will garnish a wealth of roles for her. Go to see it. You will not be disappointed and even if you don't love him as much as I do, I think you'll enjoy it."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "13cbb549-ef7f-4e15-9770-9b32d590dd9d", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:31.145286", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "1108a3a607aff32ec97e4c75241e2503d8e2cd7b5b9ace342911ff7b45050d29"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "author": "ib011f9545i", "rating": 7, "date": "2026-01-31", "title": null, "content": "If like me you like this sort of action film you will know what you will get in a film like this,but to be fair to Statham there are new angles to this film.\n\nThis is an action film set in the islands of Scotland.\n\nI won't do plot spoilers but this is not just a mindless action film,to be fair Statham makes better films than his critics will admit.\n\nThere is an impressive child actress in the film who I predict will go far.\n\nI was surprised that 2 fairly big acting names are in this as well as Statham.\n\nI would love to know exactly where this film is set because I think some of it is Scotland but some is Ireland."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "91ae6f00-4d55-4b1d-86b2-9f64a3113463", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:31.145286", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "2a7fb3bc4d592d7561654016299b47ff6777bc480377a4f6d312654242df76d7"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "author": "moviesgamesandvideos", "rating": 9, "date": "2026-01-31", "title": null, "content": "Exactly what you want from a Jason Statham film.\n\nIt takes minimal time to establish a consistent plot and then gets straight into the action, of which there are quite a few visceral, kinetic, and well shot action sequences. There is very little plot armour, a couple of times he manages to slip away which wouldn't happen in reality but it doesn't detract at all from the film. Well shot, well acted and has a well constructed plot and pacing that delivers what I think you would want from Statham. One of his best and I will be getting it on 4K to watch again. I thought it was much better than the recent Beekeeper and Working Man films."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "238d9f06-1aac-4772-9f3b-20211fd2f4ba", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:31.145286", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "2f43f3a213795516075956217ee25a5ad33c34fbb9b2a3b95c5ddd33c951f8fb"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "author": "Luv2Spooge", "rating": 4, "date": "2026-02-25", "title": null, "content": "I can't wait for AI to start producing movies because humans are really out of creativities. This movie? You've seen it before, a mix-mash of Borne Identity + Leon The Professional, without any depth or direction.\n\nJason Statham is known for his martial arts, hand to hand combat. Perhaps he is getting old that is why he is resorting to these cheap B movies using guns and stuff. The action is snoozy, the fighting is slow and uninspiring.\n\nHis last good film was Beekeeper. Rest after were Nicholas Cage level crap.\n\n4/10."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "7f2193fa-83b4-4863-b756-ddb8965029c2", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:31.145286", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "2780fd6f7db3fabf30def4a1f685326753ebb20a1c59fe2e08636079766cb8ca"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "author": "seaneveritt-63391", "rating": 7, "date": "2026-03-01", "title": null, "content": "As the title says, Jason Statham action movies are a guilty pleasure of mine that i can never get enough of. I realise there is nothing high concept or thought provoking in them but i can seek out other movies for that. If i want to just escape & unwind to a good entertaining easy watch action movie. Jason is my guy.....as consistent in their quality as a Five Guys burger or a Mickey D's breakfast. Reliable & enjoyable."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "ea612d25-8750-4fab-a23f-4d2cba2dd098", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:31.145286", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "f9d1285a4974d740f8957dbe9ed127e397c17c96f97df28e454c0d9952dce736"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "author": "aylwardpaul", "rating": 8, "date": "2026-02-08", "title": null, "content": "I was surprised to find that this is better than the usual Jason Statham fare.\n\nIt's like a Jason Bourne film, albeit the main protagonist is in hiding, rather than having lost his memory.\n\nThe direction of action scenes isn't quite as clear as in the Bourne films either, as there are too many quick cuts and close ups in the fights to offer clarity.\n\nHowever it is a thrill ride, and the next best thing to Bourne.\n\nIf you are familiar with and like most Statham films then you'll love this. It is far superior to films such as The Beekeeper.\n\nStatham is in good form, and the actress playing his girl companion is great.\n\nThe film is complete within itself, but also sets things up nicely for a possible franchise, which is good news if this standard is maintained."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "0c46adb1-c613-4513-9be9-2582e7f0b772", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:31.145286", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "08e6fb14e0ed3702adc10eb3c7e77f939fedaed620f4777faa903cefe7eced2e"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "author": "tkdlifemagazine", "rating": 7, "date": "2026-02-24", "title": null, "content": "Jason Statham has created a niche' as a a calm quiet man whose early skills are revealed when pressed. While the formula is similar in many of his films, the execution varies from good to great. Statham is a dependable screen presence and terrific actions star. This movie has a small, cozy feel but you sense early on there is more to this quiet man who is managing a lighthouse in Ireland. The film intensifies and we learn more. Like the peeling of an onion Statham's skills and past are revealed. This is really a good action movie. Well film. Well executed and directed. Bodhi Rae Breathnach Is very good as the young, orphaned sidekick. Action, fights, and gunpaly are very good here. I recommend this one."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "39799611-b2e1-4850-9516-919c7a00ab14", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:31.145286", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "7b028ee40aef03fbd7c920e2f1d07181923b47c0d88af9ca91d08f0d0174a3d7"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "author": "Stevens_Movie_Reviews", "rating": 6, "date": "2026-02-25", "title": null, "content": "Good Statham variation. Don't look for anything groundbreaking, and the quite typical storyline, action scenes, and villainy will meet your expectations.\n\nMysterious character with a secret and very dangerous past forced out of reclusion and retirement to protect both himself but more significantly, an innocent against organized and corrupt forces of death and destruction.\n\nYou get the picture; you've seen it many times before and were probably entertained by it for an hour or so most times.\n\nThis entry brings some nice scenery, and some notable cinematography. The car chases are wild and crunchy. The fight scenes are highly choreographed and precise, as is the gun play. The mood overall is serious and tense.\n\nWhat stood out most for me was the score. The soundtrack. Really good deep and gritty electronic and ambient that fit in really well throughout the whole film. Elevated it noticeably, consistently.\n\nUnsurprisingly, but still slightly eye-rolling, absurd, and obvious at this point we get a female head of state, a female of colour head of the spy agency, a female head tech wizard. And an old white man main villain. Yes, we're still doing this. These rules for getting a movie made apparently still exist even for a dark and gritty action flick.\n\nStill, definitely worth a watch for men and boys for whom movies like this are too few and far between. Check it out."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "3b9dd54e-60d6-4e47-b646-20d1c61ec2d1", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:31.145286", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "b6f6e5461afd5214026096a781ce0ba4f371606fad949728de8d1bdb608f1814"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "author": "SnoopyStyle", "rating": 7, "date": "2026-02-27", "title": null, "content": "Mason (Jason Statham) is a solo lighthouse keeper on an isolated island. Jessie and her uncle deliver the weekly supplies to the misanthropic loner. Well, that takes a turn. With that start and knowing absolutely nothing about the movie, I thought we might be doing a ghost story. I'm good with the secret agent turn. I just don't like him doing it with his Home Alone traps. He is supposed to be a super-soldier. He should have a few guns at the lighthouse. It gets better. It's the standard Statham story."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "9a1e738b-3154-4269-8a32-4c2f7f5181c4", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:31.145286", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "5194e0551668ea6e4871d35d7b1f9b1a41c1f28d936dac7bcc88d7893add3872"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "author": "drahulrajjsd", "rating": 10, "date": "2026-01-30", "title": null, "content": "Shelter is an action movie that I'm interested in watching because of 2 reasons... Firstly it's from the director of Felon (2008) and Shot Caller (2017)... Secondly you've got Jason Statham as the lead... It's in the vein of movies like Leon : The Professional (1994), Mercury Rising (1998), Safe (2012) and many more where a badass must protect a young one from the badmen... It's that formula and it's really done well... Bodhi Rae Breathnach also shines as Jesse... Great film!"}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "f953a379-dc1a-45d5-b039-cad83801d210", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:31.145286", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "d87dbad6f1be3dd6706e3014f0286743190a0c1f30e38781b2502e96ea40cf1b"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "author": "barefootstallion", "rating": 5, "date": "2026-02-24", "title": null, "content": "I am a solid fan of anything Statham. I put down everything, stop everything, shift schedules, all to be able to sit down to a good Statham-verse movie. That is simply because Statham does the fight-em-up, beat-the-bad-guys-to-pulps trope better than anybody else in the genre. But after watching this movie, I am left wondering whether it's genre-exhaustion that got me, or that this was just a poor movie. And I am left with the conclusion that it was just a poor movie.\n\nThe storyline was just. . . Convoluted. There were no real hooks to grab the viewer. Okay, girl is in trouble, wrong place wrong time and Jason has to keep her safe, and the arch villain is some pinch-faced no-gooder in a top, government position, who went sour. . . For reasons. Reasons that are never explained, and seem to be left intentionally murky to cover up the idea that the writers didn't have a clue, either.\n\nThe fight scenes were fun. They always are in Statham movies. Statham just brings a verve to them that makes them hard not to enjoy. But the story? To call it a disjointed mess would be doing it a kindness. It was difficult to follow, made little sense, and had an ending that felt like the movie was deliberately withholding a satisfying conclusion from its audience. It left me wishing that for the love of going to the movies, that Statham would sign on with people who have talent. Because this is the second outing in a row, where his style and why people come to see him, was not used effectively.\n\nI gave this 5 out of 10 only for the fighting sequences. The rest is just. . . Ugh."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "7adb91d6-65fd-4b5d-b048-fb41b59f3ea9", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:31.145286", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "07384e24833b70bf02b77c5791538dcd322903884c0e819515c68785cfbab597"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "author": "Mr_Sophistication_Uk", "rating": 5, "date": "2026-02-17", "title": null, "content": "Shelter surprised me at first. Rather than being the all-out Jason Statham action film I was expecting, it mostly shows him initially living on a remote island in Scotland with his dog, playing chess by himself and watching the tide come in. Shades of Castaway, perhaps? No volleyball, though.\n\nLater, he rescues a teenage girl from certain drowning off the coast, and together the two of them forge an unlikely friendship from tenuous beginnings. It feels intimate, personal... not words that are often use to describe the MANY genre movies Statham has made his trademark over the years.\n\nSadly, it just can't last. They end up getting discovered on a hidden camera (a running theme here) when he goes to get some medicine, and then as soon as a bunch of soldiers were sent to the island with the sole intent of taking him out, I knew we were reverting to type. Not boring exactly, and his relationship with the girl is as interesting as ever, but not the quiet little drama I hoped for based on the first third or so.\n\nFrom there, you can more-or-less predict the rest. They end up on the mainland... he tracks down an old army friend... dispatches policeman after policeman without taking a hit... the government enlists the help of a 'specialist' in tracking him down so he has a 'rival'... and so on.\n\nI think it was the scene in the London nightclub, where all hell breaks loose as he tries to rescue the girl, that I realised it had finally seagued into the kind of movie I thought I'd be getting in the beginning.\n\nAgain, nothing terrible... but something I've seen before a million times. Is originality a dirty word these days? I guess so. 5/10."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "c3498dfa-0c99-4ef0-aefe-de6ae00a66ed", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:31.145286", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "6c59441e325e2f436f5a6b5c9d13f2ecbec3dbdf46a5c47d6670615e2f93afba"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "author": "sami2005", "rating": 8, "date": "2026-03-01", "title": null, "content": "Shelter is a gripping action film that keeps you hooked from the first scene to the last. The pace is relentless, with well-choreographed fight sequences and tight, energetic direction that never allows the tension to drop. Jason Statham delivers a strong physical performance, showcasing impressive fitness and presence that perfectly suits the role. The film carries clear echoes of the Jason Bourne style-fast cuts, grounded combat, and a lone protagonist navigating danger at every turn. While the story may follow a familiar action formula, the execution is solid and consistently entertaining. Overall, Shelter is an intense and satisfying action experience."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "15fc1598-39ee-457f-b464-23286aedcd04", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:31.145286", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "729cac261dfb7b9688f162659d3223f0a8594580e27fa605433f25262ed66ef4"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "author": "donmurray29", "rating": 8, "date": "2026-02-05", "title": null, "content": "Giving this an 8/10 rating\n\nA different type of feel for a Statham film, very much grounded and not flashy at all, it's one of his better films in a while, and he's been busy. Looking grey on old with a great beard, suits Jason. Body Rae Breathnach is simply perfect in this, never seen her before, but she is very good, with what she's given to do. The cast is well up to the job as the action and who feel of the film from director Ric Roman Waugh, is rough and ready.\n\nWard parry gives us a seedy look into the UK intelligence network, and this is his take on it. Bill Nighy and Naomi Ackie have fun with their characters, and good old Daniel Mays pops up. This film is very much different from what I expected and it was such a change, it gets a high score for it, music is great so listen out."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "2c49a49c-48f1-4970-a730-a296965e227f", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:31.145286", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "acc86c095f13337ded12fc9c7f678c42431fb34e48c5e8711157cf3b713b1bfd"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "author": "Jimcage316", "rating": 8, "date": "2026-02-27", "title": null, "content": "After beekeeper and working man I didn't think statham would make a movie as good as wrath of man but I'm glad I'm wrong this film was great it takes time to develop the story before the action kicks in and boy does it ever this was a thrill watching this the action choreography was soo well done and I like the chemistry statham has with the young lady this is everything you can ever want from an action film pure adrenaline rush watching it him defeating these spooks and saving the life of an innocent girl i thoroughly enjoyed this film i cant recommend shelter enough and so far imo its the best film of the year."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "9ffe3fac-99e1-453b-9aa5-87f54203593f", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:31.145286", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "02ad965d90210f50abed4e3238b3e7c6386e7182e8a2fb67ec8973a1592aa817"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "author": "stevendbeard", "rating": 8, "date": "2026-01-31", "title": null, "content": "I saw Shelter, starring Jason Statham-The Beekeeper, Ghosts of Mars; Bodhi Rae Breathnach-Hamnet, So Awkward Academy_tv; Naomi Ackie-Mickey 17, Master of None_tv and Bill Nighy-The First Omen, Hot Fuzz.\n\nThis is a typical Jason Statham action flick so don't be expecting anything different. Of course, I love his action movies so there is nothing wrong with that. Jason lives in an isolated lighthouse on an island and gets his groceries delivered by boat. Bodhi is the delivery girl-her uncle drives the boat to the island-and when a storm capsizes the boat after a delivery, Jason saves Bodhi but her uncle drowns. Jason, a former spy that was presumed to be dead for 10 years-that's why he is hiding in a lighthouse-reluctantly nurses Bodhi back to health but when he goes to town for supplies, he is caught on camera and his past comes back to haunt him. Bill plays Jason's old boss that wants him dead and Naomi plays the new head of MI6. There are a lot of fights-Duh-as Jason tries to evade Bill's men and Jason is also trying to protect Bodhi, who was an innocent caught in the crossfire.\n\nIt's rated R for violence and language and has a running time of 1 hour & 47 minutes.\n\nIf you like Jason Statham movies, you should enjoy this one too. I did and would buy it on Blu_Ray."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "dea5af06-092d-4539-be88-5fb42f1691c5", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:31.145286", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "362b9564bb10db6eb09a764956c77c6af986479939abd320ae7c5cdcdde9ec3d"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "author": "sgreviewedthat", "rating": 8, "date": "2026-02-27", "title": null, "content": "So many past movies melded together to create a perfect breeding ground for a 2 to 4 movie run...you watch the girl grow up and him secretly always protect her from the enemies of his past...UNTIL...he finally ends it once and for all...JS at his best...everyone in the movie is great...it's a \"multiwatch\" (i will watch it multiple times...3 already)...well done!"}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "893258de-3d96-4654-a828-1c46dd3c4898", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:31.145286", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "f1de4ac9190973331b553bc4073b89466a71490ae18b15e033bec08e45ce86b0"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "author": "Tomaslillebror", "rating": 8, "date": "2026-02-25", "title": null, "content": "For starters the acting is great from all parts but especially amazing by Jason Statham and his co-lead Bodhi Rae, the girl he saves. This movie shows Statham at his best.\n\nThe director did a well measured job with this movie. It starts out slow but after five minutes its depth in every clip and no time is wasted. The action flies between moments of sensibility that likely will cause you too tear up inside\n\nTechnically well made, music and sound is especially great.\n\nIts not a complicated story, this is no thriller but you wont get boored, yet it has a great depth, especially communicated through the great acting and music.\n\nIf there is something that could have been improved its a broader story in nicer surroundings than the North sea in winter and no token black girl.\n\n8/10."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "ad3bd12a-ac48-46ed-903d-8f344269636f", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:31.145286", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "979cdf818f98b56e9394131fbdffeb02229a50866a9a94b908c03357831da2d8"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "author": "nattie32", "rating": 9, "date": "2026-02-04", "title": null, "content": "The best part of movie was lots action true Statham form. The story was a little meh but the action makes up for it. Finally a kid in a movie who is not annoying she was actually a good actress. Bonus no unwanted useless love scenes. The ending kind of leaves it open that there could be a sequel. Overall if you like action movies definitely a watch."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "29961426-9d41-4452-a7ba-faed8c59963f", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:31.147318", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "f42a77543ae220b0dd1204d4dee5ae89e3569a11e9c2c6f6fdb96adc000652fc"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "author": "pszeto1", "rating": 7, "date": "2026-03-01", "title": null, "content": "Many of Statham's past films typically set up his \"past\" within the first little while. This one, feels it took longer than it should. Once that was established, the flow through the remaining acts was uneven. When the action starts pace was better. Minding you almost stopped watching it due to the dog incident which I thought was sad and unnecessary. Because of this, you'll notice few further subtle flavours of \"John Wick\".. Like the scene in the dance club plus the overall plotline - get to the one who started it all. If you're a big Statham fan, it'll be in your wheelhouse but may rank this little lower than average among his list of movie credits."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "e34db27a-9569-4103-ac2c-7a7ce51ac4ac", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:31.147318", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "a20437a977a989c26e258cbd423aa52cde8a0b05d57c52b38fe96db73f8da790"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "author": "krizst", "rating": 7, "date": "2026-02-24", "title": null, "content": "Bodhi Rae Breathnach is a definite screen entity. She has all the makings of a quality actress and did a great job in this film alongside of Statham who also was darn good. I enjoyed this and it was a reasonable if a pretty normal plot line. The only aspect that was so terribly bad was the pathetic ending. Killing off the head of MI6 ie Nigh was just stupid. If Statham the character was really interested in creating a safety for his girl he would have accepted the offer to rejoin the force and be on the side of the tribe ie his government because the other sides don't play nice. Grow up and stop being afraid of the brutality of real life. Depict it."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "82555e4b-8491-4f69-a875-53135b4251be", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:31.147318", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "ba258852eb5ac37750db08eb9ab5730d57e380f6fcbdfb5b2a9b36d05b080860"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "author": "Jim_Screechy", "rating": 7, "date": "2026-03-03", "title": null, "content": "If your a Jason Statham fan then you have a pretty good idea what you're in for. This is a really enjoyable movie, and though I think it could have been better, It's still a great movie you can lose yourself in, and lives up to the hyper action thriller genre as you expect.\n\nIt' is a bit slow in the begining and takes a few minutes to get going. To be honest, I'm not sure that this time spent laying the groundwork esstablishes a solid enough foundation for what's to come, espcially given the time that allotted to it. Still we get to the meat and bones of the story after about 20 mins where things pick up and never really slacken.\n\nThe fight scenes are great. The choreograhy which in some movies can be poorly rendered and somewhat unconvincing is nice and tight. None of that close-up camera work the tries to hide the actual action or fast changing camera perspectives that poorly attempt to simulate action. Here Its solid, well shot and convincing.\n\nThe story is a great too, I'm glad they decided to give the screenplay some real 'legs' and not let the action bare the weight of the tale. It's contemporary, relevant and one that is easy to relate to wihout being cheesy, romanticised or overly familiar. Things play out well, but I think they should have dealt a little more with the underlying story rather than just let it drift into the ethos. They dealt primarily with the consequences of the issue rather than the underlying cause and this leaves the satisfaction of resolution a little vacant. Thus I never really got the feeling that the story was fleshed out as well as it could have been. There was more to be done with it, and the carcass of the story was left with too many good cuts of meat ripe for exploiting.\n\nI think the run time was a little short and probably should have been extened just past the two hour span. I know this is a restriction some ventures don't like to exceed, but sometimes, when a story is a good one, as it is here, it can add a great deal of value to the experience rather than detract from it... which is what I think happens here to some extent. There were some threads left unexplored and some characters feeling a little sidelined to the detriment of the movie; by the time the credits were rolling I felt a little unsatiated, which is something Staham films usually get right, but sadly not here.\n\nStill it's a good film and I thoroughly enjoyed it.\n\nFor what's on offer I'd give it an 8, but I'm taking a point off because there was more on offer here than they actually delivered.\n\n7/10 from me."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "beb278c4-9c76-4cb9-bd07-579b544e783e", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:31.147318", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "c2fff99b00633a5bf46f5c4c5517b116d5fded28eaeaed7a6e4a4963a66ec837"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "author": "Maverick_1332", "rating": 7, "date": "2026-01-31", "title": null, "content": "Not sure if it's damning with faint praise to say I didn't hate it. It may have taken a little longer than I liked to get going but once it did there was the anticipated body count with the bad guys coming in for some serious stick. There may have been a few questions you would have liked to ask about the plot points but at 1 hour 47 minutes it did not outstay its welcome. Bodhi Rae Breathnach deserves a special mention as I thought she was excellent as the spirited young girl who was a key part of the action."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "45684015-b465-4cbc-9117-34ad037c325f", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:31.147318", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "7030b6b37522b033c9c7c65e4ab39f8d5a257b14a5ece4b313f8c7ef8ce7a6c1"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "author": "jinp-55", "rating": 1, "date": "2026-02-04", "title": null, "content": "Soul-less movie that's all I can say. It is a basic story line since ages that hero need to protect a gal or heroine and do some random fights and kill the villain that's all. Not sure why Jason Statham being a popular Hollywood star chose a boring story line like this instead of exploring horror or super natural or spiritual story lines at his age."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "49266395-cc9a-49ae-95a3-511a0186bde7", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:31.147318", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "5dc4859dc883603013e798d64fa66f79987500f361568e1513425c1373354fd4"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "author": "bruinsandchiefs", "rating": 10, "date": "2026-01-31", "title": null, "content": "Statham movies are like Comfort Foods: Yeah, they're a known quantity, but films like \"Shelter\" take those old recipes and still give us a tasty, highly satisfying meal.\n\nBorrowing a little from his own back catalog (especially \"Safe\" & \"Hummingbird\"), Statham is a former assassin who turned his back on that life for ... reasons.\n\nAnd now, people from that former life are trying to kill him.\n\nAdd in a little girl in danger*, and we all know what's coming: he'll kill the Bad Guys AND get her to safety, ...or die trying.\n\n*BTW: The girl (Bodhi Rae Breathnach) is adorable, and a fine little actress.\n\nWhile the action scenes are excellent, it's the slowly mounting tension throughout that keeps your attention.\n\nYou don't get to truly relax until the very end.\n\nIs it \"Gone With The Wind\", or \"The Godfather\"? Nope.\n\nBut c'mon: it's not SUPPOSED to be.\n\nIt's a solid 9-out-of-10 on my \"I'd Watch It Again\" scale."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "270b6f16-b352-458c-bd05-f36ec9055459", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:31.147318", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "2522cf76f9347f2c0ea7031cf1c8a903ecbfe1bf2ab9d96e517c65bc4513df19"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "author": "kentchurch", "rating": 9, "date": "2026-02-08", "title": null, "content": "Another Statham flick. Another solid action entry.\n\nYes, Shelter is nothing we haven't seen before but this Statham outing is less choreographed and more natural than previous outings.\n\nThe little girl who is his co star is quite good and the film is handsomely made.\n\nThe action you ask?\n\nCool and excellent.\n\nStatham delivers the goods again. It's all very well put together and brutal and hardcore.\n\nShelter doesn't reinvent the wheel but it's fun and a welcome distraction from the mega budget dross out there. A simple, pleasant evenings entertainment.\n\nAs long as Statham keeps making em, I'll keep watching em."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "91fe20de-8a84-4018-bd00-0787dab5c65a", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:31.147318", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "9f28938e5b460806c98d486d6f25b234a76f73de128ad502b01e96c2fd8c52b8"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "author": "1RandomFan", "rating": 7, "date": "2026-03-01", "title": null, "content": "Shelter is exactly what you expect when you sit down for a new Jason Statham movie - gritty fights, intense standoffs, and a lead character who doesn't say much but lets his fists do most of the talking.\n\nI really enjoyed this one. It doesn't break any new ground in the action genre and it definitely plays things safe. If you've seen a few Statham films before, you'll recognize the formula almost immediately. There aren't many surprises, and the story follows a pretty familiar path.\n\nThat said, sometimes familiar works.\n\nThe movie is a little slow getting started. The first act takes its time setting up the situation, and it might test your patience just a bit. But once things kick into gear, it delivers exactly what it promises - solid, hard-hitting action sequences and some well-choreographed fight scenes.\n\nStatham carries the film with his usual screen presence. He knows this role inside and out, and even when the script doesn't give him much to work with emotionally, he still makes the character compelling enough to root for.\n\nOverall, Shelter is a good, action-packed time. It may not reinvent the wheel, but it doesn't need to. If you're looking for a straightforward, no-nonsense action movie, this one gets the job done."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "40930ab0-036b-44fe-ad7f-5f8d2371d0d6", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:31.147318", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "be62415043eac19a90a49e6a91058cfbdbf020087c711bcf03ec379acda67041"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "author": "UniqueParticle", "rating": 7, "date": "2026-02-04", "title": null, "content": "Jason Statham is genius at one man army action and nice how much dialogue he in this he's lovely at protecting someone. Shelter doesn't deserve hate it's a great blast of entertainment, the girl was wonderful, and stylish action with along with dance club scene was so good! This movie had barely much advertisements quite shocked of that seems unusual for Jason Statham film but fun stuff would recommend."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "3ed9915d-2fad-49a0-b511-cfd9367d3dda", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:31.147318", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "8d10d9a0334aa7767a79ed9c1264bef7f528c5f3c760077a6f3e45dd727fb4f6"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "author": "Almazbekov99", "rating": 10, "date": "2026-03-01", "title": null, "content": "An amazing exploration of the mind of the solitary lighthouse keeper.\n\nWhen I started watching I initially thought 'oh no , another lighthouse movie'. Think the Lighthouse 1 ,2,3 , In the lighthouse, on the lighthouse , the lighthouse family etc etc. There are simply too many and going over the same standard formula.\n\nThis one totally threw me. Statham , typically known for action movies, really portrays a mentally ill lone lighthouse keeper superbly.\n\nThe movie delves deep into his inner mind and possible haluicinations. I say possible because the movie ending leaves so many questions, such as was it all a dream , was it all imagined in a daydream etc etc. The ending is a complete cliffhanger, paving the way for a sequel or prequel or even a musical."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "bee73138-5f0c-412a-ba18-ce5e8ae8326f", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:31.147318", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "b9ee5d4f9b2d26220f3605da1d66f85110d2ce9d11c0e2db1d1ff4784995f849"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "author": "Ac1975", "rating": 1, "date": "2026-02-02", "title": null, "content": "Statham really made his name churning up dozens of boring, by the numbers action B/C class movies for many years in a row now. In these never-ending low budget stories he always plays the same tough guy with the same face expression and the same story. This movie is exactly as the 100 previous ones. I would go crazy doing the this kind of brain-numbing stuff over and over again but Statham does not seem to mind. We need something new and refreshing."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "80b913e8-0b4e-4741-9921-767198f1e890", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:31.147318", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "bf69c0ae5baa03afd586616ab610c24683b34f916d36067feb27bedeb131303a"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "author": "asanmihaicatalin", "rating": 7, "date": "2026-02-04", "title": null, "content": "The recipe works again, and Jason Statham easily fulfills the role that suits him best. For his fans and not only, the character of the lone wolf to whom a child becomes attached and vice versa, guarantees success.\n\nJessie, the little girl played by Bodhi Rae, is a cutie and plays very well.. The rest? Action in the characteristic style of Statham, a tireless actor.\n\nThe film is a must-see for fans and not only."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "18cbd960-5c19-4de9-91fb-5b390ba831dc", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:31.147318", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "15910fc932f9f2f9dc97bf6a93bcd8cb17306cd0042f037c77a229324fd03ace"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "author": "redban02", "rating": 7, "date": "2026-02-05", "title": null, "content": "I went to see \"Shelter\" on 02/04/2026. I like it overall.\n\nThe movie's main asset, obviously, is Statham. As always, he's cool, likable, and credible. Even if he's playing the same character that he always plays, his performance doesn't feel diminished or stale. If any other actor had been in his place, I would've given this movie a 4-5/10. With Statham, though, I go for a 7.0/10\n\nThe action scenes, which are plentiful, are fine. Some of them remind me of John Wick, particularly at the end. And that's no flaw: I love the Wick movies\n\nA big part of the movie involves Statham's relationship with the girl. And I think it works. Some of their scenes are heartwarming. The little girl looks adorable, and she never gets annoying (as many characters of her ilk often do)\n\nI have a few gripes with the movie. The core plot with Statham and the little girl works, but the other main plot centers on the British government. Here, the scenes focus on a villain named Manaford and an ambiguous woman named Roberta. I found these government scenes to be slow and unsatisfying. The woman who plays Roberta is not a good actress\n\nThe finale is completely by-the-numbers. Along the way, Statham and the little girl are pursued by some soldier. This soldier comes off like a Temu-Terminator in his behavior ... there are some corny and lazily written lines (\"You care about her?,\" one character asks Statham in a syrupy exchange).\n\n7.0/10."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "dbcaa8d8-b14d-40fe-a7fa-125046576029", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:31.147318", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "8a4a1233655c69794d0781ec12babc29116a9f7b06704899f2279aa389048c4f"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "author": "DarkSpotOn", "rating": 5, "date": "2026-02-15", "title": null, "content": "Biggest negative for this movie is the intro, the intro didn't need to be that long that whole first segment could of been cut to like 10 minutes the pacing at the beginning is really the biggest issue with this movie. Minus the start, everything else kinda works.\n\nThe acting is soild, camera work is fine, plot is okay a bit questionable but alright, it's a decent action movie. Another kinda negative i got is the fact that the movie repeats itself pretty much you're in a loop hole that just keeps repeating. Once the shooting (guns) start, it just keeps repeating it's self over and over and over again. Personally i'd rather watch something like Pulp Fiction or Cold Fish or Vengeance, or Kill Bill, or Lady Vengeance, or I saw Devil i can probably keep listing names..."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "f50a2d08-2646-4af2-93fd-084cd1355c36", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:31.147318", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "5317011dd0f981397657c779a5f64421c684c12a1e6bfd26ebcb707b13da70e2"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "author": "slynnehensley", "rating": 7, "date": "2026-01-31", "title": null, "content": "*SPOILER ALERT*\n\nThe dog dies. I don't know why this needed to be part of the story. Movies are make believe, they could have easily given the dog a different outcome.\n\nIt covers everything else we love about his movies - good action scenes, murderous rampage, and ultimately satisfying ending. Still going to be mad about the dog until his next movie comes out."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "22ba48b3-940d-4b04-8b9a-b7740d3cc4f1", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:31.147318", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "8dce5e5dedc1f1873da534cf832957f8f31816fe9d4a2b20618eab8860f8bcc0"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "author": "arungeorge13", "rating": 5, "date": "2026-02-25", "title": null, "content": "I was really loving this for the first 40 minutes or so, until the film got action-heavy, thereafter treading the one-man-saviour style of a typical Statham actioner. The first act is an interpersonal drama, and one that oddly works.. if only the writing didn't suddenly switch over to a derivative MI6 elite operative gone rogue plotline. That part, while reasonably well-staged thanks to director Ric Roman Waugh, suffers from tedium. Because we've seen that way too many times by now. Statham, in a lowbrow drama, taking care of a little girl without using guns or fists, sounds a lot more interesting to me in the current cinematic climate. In the existing format, Statham and Liam Neeson feel easily interchangeable, with action and predictable villainy taking centerstage. Bodhi Rae Breathnach (as the little girl Jessie) is making a mark with this and Hamnet. Naomie Ackie and Bill Nighy appear in forgettable roles.\n\nP. S. This is a solid improvement over the director's Greenland 2: Migration, which was also released in Jan 2026."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "6abd6650-6dba-4925-b038-6f5d4dab945a", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:31.147318", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "7ffae1d10faccd5dde5abd1c05b2f60e51a824f97b9438a7b9df1b04add99500"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "author": "daisukereds", "rating": 5, "date": "2026-02-25", "title": null, "content": "Mysterious guy living in an island is forced to act in order to keep a child safe from his past mistakes.\n\nI'll be frank. The movie is perfectly okay.. but is that good enough? Considering how slow the pacing is, how dull and unfun its developments, and how safe it is.. I'd say it wasn't worth my time. But I do admit that the kid does a perfect job at playing the role assigned to her. Statham is more brooding and quiet than usual, even if still quite professional.\n\nUltimately, the film isn't fun, interesting or memorable in any way.. but it does what it sets out to do."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "bb1a8619-210b-459e-864c-77cef3f6ced8", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:31.147318", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "87129a66cdf35bbcdc4bda0a4cfa8ac465a6fe978f955c9961ae487053c9d875"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "author": "paul_m_haakonsen", "rating": 5, "date": "2026-03-06", "title": null, "content": "Of course needed no persuasion to sit down and watch the 2026 action thriller \"Shelter\", as I had the opportunity to do so. It was, after all, a movie with Jason Statham in the lead. And he usually tends to deliver good old fashioned wholesome action-packed entertainment.\n\nThe storyline in \"Shelter\" was a bit mundane. I mean, it was essentially just one long chase scene, and there wasn't really much of anything else going on. Expect very little in terms of character development, plot twists and the likes. Writer Ward Parry didn't exactly put together a script that proved overly great. Sure, it was watchable, but it was a bit generic and it most definitely wasn't among the better of Jason Statham movies.\n\nThe acting performances in \"Shelter\" were fair. It wasn't as if the movie was boasting a lot of familiar actors or actresses on the cast list. I do actually think that I was only familiar with Jason Statham and Bill Nighy.\n\nThere is an okay amount of action sequences in the movie to help the movie tread water and stay afloat.\n\nUltimately, I found \"Shelter\" to be a forgettable movie from Statham, and I seriously doubt that I will ever pick up a second time.\n\nMy rating of director Ric Roman Waugh's 2026 movie \"Shelter\" lands on a five out of ten stars."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "be9cbaee-0357-4707-a4ca-3674fc3970c1", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:31.147318", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "e9bd2331abed29782304dc570c52d3768bcb7287d722445bf53ac5557e202e82"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "author": "bombersflyup", "rating": 5, "date": "2026-02-26", "title": null, "content": "Shelter is an action-focused film, with good action sequences and music accompaniment. Statham being Statham, with Mason and Jessie making a nice little team, for what it is. The beginning very dragged out though and the alternative points of view, have no presence.\n\nCan't really do anything to combat that sort of precise auto-detect surveillance."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "c4ad9acc-493f-4c64-be79-0dd929591098", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:31.147318", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "108292ebbc1cb3d9d470c48ef84b53c44b8a8a1bb2b2fb554e22a9868666ad96"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "author": "avibernstein-52293", "rating": 9, "date": "2026-01-30", "title": null, "content": "SHELTER is a no-holds-barred adrenaline rush that proves Jason Statham remains the gold standard of modern action cinema. A relentless, muscle-tight thriller that hits with the precision and fury of a sledgehammer. Channeling John Wick-level intensity while fully owning its own brutal identity, the film unleashes bone-crunching choreography, razor-sharp pacing, and a ferocious lead performance that barely pauses for breath. Statham is in peak form: controlled, lethal, and magnetic, powering through waves of enemies with old-school authority. Seeing it in Dubai in a packed theater, with the crowd fully locked in, cheering and reacting to every hit and turn, only confirmed it: SHELTER doesn't reinvent action, it perfects it, delivering exactly what audiences want and then some more! Insane."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "e6fc742b-e54e-4ba0-a7c1-0c32fdad903e", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:31.147318", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "8e36fa03f05c16bbff0095f9bece0097e6e449af68b3c7974ee2c8c8c47d263b"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "author": "novangoghmusic", "rating": 9, "date": "2026-02-01", "title": null, "content": "This is a film that delivers all the action that fans would expect. But at the same time it also has a heart. And a very well written story. All the performances are great. The story moved along at a good pace, but without rushing.\n\nIt reminds me of one of his earlier films \"Redemption\". I will definitely buy this one when it becomes available."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "7b8efaea-0929-4720-af8c-5df0eab9b215", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:31.147318", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "080c81322e92b808c6601ee164901f33b3fa9997b1b456b032c5c74d707f5e9e"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "author": "merlincym", "rating": 8, "date": "2026-02-12", "title": null, "content": "OK, cards on the table, I like Jason Statham. There's something about him that appeals to the inner man in me. But this film, IMO, is a step up from his normal, bang, bosh, wallop style. The first half hour or so he does little else other than be moody.....and who does moody better than our Jason.\n\nThe story line, meh, usual good guy, bad guy, naughty government, and it all comes right in the end. No spoilers there - it's Jason after all. But the telling of it, excellent.\n\nAll the characters casting was top notch and the entire film watchable from start to finish.\n\nA solid 8 from me."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "06e8fb25-5b98-4488-8138-959c30821a8c", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:31.147318", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "5bbd25b0cb0c87e63f4266caef5705b1ff86f0a5a2e38cb152183721add61a72"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "author": "RobotsUprising", "rating": 1, "date": "2026-02-27", "title": null, "content": "I am not sure why it ever received ratings over 5-6 stars. It was so boring, and there was no story of any sort. In the end it is just a mindless tired rehashed clone of many other movies in this genre. There is no depth or substance to this. As a matter of fact the first 20 minutes is just mind numbingly boring, you would be more entertained watching paint dry."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "17bd5814-69fa-4649-98fb-d5a381aeb03d", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:31.147978", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "8c8d014dbfa4cacbe931b6675e158a35d2a59dd6bc8c8810157817b48faa71d0"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "author": "ztpbrmhw", "rating": 7, "date": "2026-02-05", "title": null, "content": "Yes. The movie follows the typical formula we've come to expect of late with Jason Statham films. But I couldn't help feeling this particular movie follows the Jason Bourne formula as well - nearly beat for beat.\n\nAgain we have the corrupt off the grid villain director of elite assassins who find out star is now a liability after he failed to carry out a mission. And again he's the best of the best - a \"precision instrument.\"\n\nHere Naomi Ackie - who by the way was grossly underutilized - as the Julia Stiles character, who was working behind the scenes to protect the hero while trying to figure out which one of her bosses has a nefarious intentions.\n\nAnd similar to Clive Owens (and others in other films), we have a nearly equally trained assassin out to get the hero running in parallel with everybody else.\n\nThe girl adds a nice layer to the movie, though I thought the movie was leading up to some plot twist where the girl is SOMEBODY'S daughter. But nope. Apparently just a random niece. Though don't be surprised if we see her again or we learn there's more to her story."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "f157e9ee-3181-417b-9bc9-85753dbdc9cb", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:31.147978", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "b57870d5e3ea13135b0999fbbc24bccad0ffdb88402c93a0568341197063a9d1"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "author": "tomsettles", "rating": 8, "date": "2026-02-01", "title": null, "content": "Great script and very well made movie. Statham is excellent, and all of the supporting cast are great. The whole movie takes place in England and Spain, which was nice to see vs. Being filmed in USA. It does cut off a bit abruptly at the end. I would have like to see more running time devoted to wrapping up the movie. 8/10."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "68c4a16f-f4ba-49ba-a0ce-9ab07db2db11", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:31.147978", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "a3358a57f0f7e7678f2869540bf6eb8143124429cc9f3fd28eb6f32e2410d369"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "author": "Scar38", "rating": 10, "date": "2026-03-09", "title": null, "content": "I don't care what the negative reviews say, I absolutely loved this film, I loved the lighthouse setting at the start and it just got better and better. I've always said Jason Statham isn't the best actor but he's brilliant at what he does, action, but in this his acting is really good, and Brodhi Rae Breathnach was fantastic as the vulnerable teen Michael chose to protect, she steels the show.\n\nThe only slight problem I had was the ending, it's a shame they didn't reunite, unless there is going to be a sequel.... Yes Please."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "9e1e35ea-9f9e-4690-bd90-82f7bb89d091", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:31.147978", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "d55ffd028c67aba43443df243910c850821a1d1488228149f54a5659c1fb545f"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "author": "skylerkennethkidd", "rating": 7, "date": "2026-02-18", "title": null, "content": "It took me a minute to get into the theme and setting of this movie. It may be because it was my third movie in a row in theater or it may have just been a weird introduction that didnt feel very personal. However as it gets rolling I soon get very mentally involved in the story and enjoyed the ride. Their may be many movies like this, even with the same actor, but i still enjpy it. This was not much different. Nothing better than the rest, just your standard.\n\nWatched at AMC on 2-16-2026."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "c1c83f37-aca7-4030-8208-380b899c1688", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:31.147978", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "622cb8abea745ae31642c05a9ca1205d7fa45dfe22367c8bfe4b1b79d8799b26"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "author": "pixrox1", "rating": 7, "date": "2026-02-12", "title": null, "content": "About the only thing that it accomplishes in the end is the transfer of ownership for one chess piece. This film script seems to be written by SPECTRA, as it's carefully crafted to portray MI6 as the root of all evil, thoroughly rogue from top to bottom. Furthermore, all of this agency's top assassins prove to be totally deficient against any of their dropouts with principles and a rudimentary understanding of civilized behavior. However, there's way too much collateral damage to empathize with anyone involved in this blood-letting."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "cf21931e-9ead-4b99-a238-d27db76d3323", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:31.147978", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "910a0b75a413d05bae8d731975ca103a1307785b4804981c9a44d95643c05581"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "author": "Icantthinkofaname4", "rating": 8, "date": "2026-02-01", "title": null, "content": "A well-made, high-stakes, and moderately intense Action/Spy thriller movie with powerful performances coming mostly from Jason Statham, with brutal and bloody action sequences that are gonna keep your eyes on the screen until the end of the movie.\n\nVarying from most Jason Statham action movie Shelter actually has a well written plot that the movie goes along with pretty smoothly, with a very nice story to make sure you can at least wrap you head around the movie. But once again, it's a Jason Statham action movie, there isn't going to be a well written drama movie.\n\nAlso if you're in the cinema watching this movie, don't be surprised if you've probably already seen this exact same movie like at least 30 times."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "4656066e-5460-4b32-b4ab-8a6cfff5831f", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:31.147978", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "aa274a66f94b7bbc481c833ffebf62ec68332dccfe1d8fe916e1f364a4635a13"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "author": "chand-suhas", "rating": 5, "date": "2026-01-30", "title": null, "content": "A mystery man is living on an island with his dog, working at a non-functioning lighthouse. His supplies are delivered by Jessie and her uncle. She is displeased at the mystery man's behavior and on one such visits, she gets caught in a storm. With no other choice, the mystery man rescues her and tends to her injury. As they bond, his identity is revealed to his former agency and thus, Michael Mason is forced to come out of his self imposed retirement, in order to protect Jessie. How does this one man army unleashes wrath on his attackers while protecting Jessie, forms rest of the story.\n\nWard Parry has written a story which is tailor made for Jason Statham. He is not tasked with doing much but deliver his usual restrained performance with enough punches to be thrown around. It is the supporting cast that becomes the added advantage as it is just fun to watch Bill Nighy play the antagonist. The short runtime keeps the narrative fast paced as there are action blocks at regular intervals. The drama isn't overdone as Mason being Jessie's guardian and their bond works well. Even though the film offers nothing new and the climax action is a bit underwhelming, this new Jason Statham is still a decent one time watch, courtesy the starcast."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "c4260b49-24bd-49d3-a299-19b35146f4c8", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:31.147978", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "d233c633e993cc727f37a387816fe2503d36f9fd9e03096bbaef025ce8402a03"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "author": "Narrative_Distance", "rating": 8, "date": "2026-02-24", "title": null, "content": "Shelter doesn't aim to be a layered drama or socially charged narrative and it doesn't need to be. What it delivers is focused, well-executed action that knows its audience and delivers precisely what it promises.\n\nJason Statham brings his trademark intensity and physical presence, giving weight to a character defined more by action than dialogue. The film emphasizes practical, grounded fight sequences and tension-filled set pieces rather than overblown visual effects, making each confrontation feel immediate and impactful.\n\nEmerging talent Bodhi Rae Breathnach impresses in a supportive role, demonstrating emotional nuance alongside the lead, while Bill Nighy contributes gravitas and presence, even in limited screen time.\n\nThe story itself is familiar and predictable, but Shelter succeeds because it is clear about its intentions: entertainment first, complexity optional. Not every film needs to reinvent the genre to be satisfying; disciplined execution, strong performances, and well-crafted action can make for a thoroughly enjoyable experience.\n\nIt is not a masterpiece, nor does it aim to be. What it achieves is focused, engaging action delivered with clarity and energy: a strong example of modern action cinema executed well."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "e3a2a0b2-c2f3-40d3-9f91-3e574be0c466", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:31.147978", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "cf82e0567bb93e5c7b19d4f83fcfff053bd3653bc75180886b3554301c25470e"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "author": "Nooner777", "rating": 9, "date": "2026-02-01", "title": null, "content": "When you see the name above the title and man on the cover art work you can already see what to expect.\n\nNow imagine 007 went rogue and on the run in hiding and was called out of retirement because some kids made a tik tok.\n\nSocial media is everywhere and so are cameras in every aspect of life. I'm going to note the version I saw was an advanced screening where the little girl had big reveal as to why Statham is so protective. The second viewing I had was when it opened and the character is left ambiguous. Ambiguity works best. This one has a story and heart to it all. His reason for caring is both personal and redeeming. I have to say I really enjoyed this movie I saw it twice."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "04d7a6cb-c654-45f6-bcfb-6b11b71b84ff", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:31.147978", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "3ae3c11aaef56f21c0beda8a7ac32711f9c98722be91d0345da1d1dfe3cd2be6"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "author": "mersinkarisik", "rating": 10, "date": "2026-02-03", "title": null, "content": "Shelter delivers exactly what a Jason Statham-led action film should: tight pacing, grounded action, and a central performance driven by physical presence and restraint. Jason Statham operates firmly within his established range, but does so with confidence and control.\n\nThe film benefits from a clear narrative focus, avoiding unnecessary subplots and keeping momentum high throughout. The bond between Statham's character and the young girl provides a functional emotional core without tipping into sentimentality, giving the story added weight amid the violence and tension.\n\nDirector Ric Roman Waugh opts for a straightforward, disciplined approach. Action sequences are coherent, practical, and efficiently edited, favoring realism over excess. While Shelter does not attempt to redefine the genre, it shows respect for classic action storytelling and executes it with professionalism.\n\nFor viewers who appreciate traditional, well-crafted action thrillers with a steady tone and a reliable lead, Shelter is a solid and entertaining entry."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "0d333cab-7385-4bf6-8cfb-1db51d97103d", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:31.147978", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "abc225a18d442f1fc367aa3d6d7b4b28e549ae36d875d1c2550cb244061f22c4"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "author": "barathbushan", "rating": 10, "date": "2026-02-04", "title": null, "content": "Simple, straight to the point without any convoluted plots. Dude just saves a young girl from bad guys, nothing much more to it. It would be nice watch with the whole family. Great action sequences. Heartwarming relationship growth. If at all the movie lacks, its that there could be more backstory needed on the guy, but hopefully it's a sequel."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "62992486-18af-46be-add4-36526448ce4c", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:31.147978", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "fb8b8733d99b97a2fcef1b7e297d95800c3830cd9986a3db0f2b401f4b5a2c72"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "author": "drael64", "rating": 7, "date": "2026-02-25", "title": null, "content": "This film has a great opening, that uses effective story writing to sell the Statham's character and the emergent protector relationship. It's cinematically sound, and initially slow moving. Really sets things up well.\n\nFrom there, the action is, it's good, but it's a little on the 'creative' side. So not as grounded as the setting generally otherwise is. The soundtracking is great, the story from there is effective, although not quite as good as the opening. Satisfying, but could have used more of those slower careful moments from the open rather than falling back to British spy series/movie type defaults.\n\nOverall good and you won't be bored, but not exceptional either. However those better moments, show a subtlety to Statham's acting which could could use more air, and was appreciated."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "00a9b686-f042-43a6-946f-2d12b385069d", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:31.147978", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "eeaea1dd6f5363d0c935278788ff2f1d3c09225a35224f3542a3a60607e809c2"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "author": "movieman6-413-929510", "rating": 3, "date": "2026-01-30", "title": null, "content": "Shelter is a new action thriller directed by Ric Roman Waugh, the director of the two Greenland films.\n\nA recluse (Jason Statham) lives on a remote Scottish island and occasionally receives new supplies, which are delivered by a girl named Jesse (Bodhi Rae Breathnach). When she delivers supplies again during a storm, her ship sinks and the recluse is forced to rescue her.\n\nHe ends up taking care of Jesse, while at the same time being confronted once again by dark figures from his past. He is forced to face that past while trying to keep Jesse safe.\n\nFor the director, this film was released in January alongside Greenland: Migration. It appears that he directed both films almost simultaneously, which may partly explain the messy aspects of Shelter. For instance, it is quite obvious that the storm Jesse gets caught in was filmed using CGI on a green screen.\n\nIn addition, the screenplay was written by a writer for whom this is only his second project, something that is noticeable in the unclear narrative structure. The story feels chaotic and is therefore difficult to follow, making it hard to take the film seriously. Ultimately, it remains a standard Jason Statham action movie that you don't have to think too much about.\n\nThe action scenes are entertaining, but not always very realistic. Unfortunately, they are also not all filmed very clearly, so it's not always easy to follow the over-the-top ways in which Jason Statham defeats his enemies.\n\nDespite this, Jason Statham is once again entertaining as an action star. Had he been given a clearer story, the viewer would have had more reason to sympathize with him. Due to the messy execution of the film, Bodhi Rae Breathnach also doesn't always come across as strongly as she could have."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "20367b16-feca-405c-afd4-eef33869cb6b", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:31.147978", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "357f664911ac36dddb23b41b7075cdce4274592e8641cddc476aecb202191d5b"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "author": "lord_orsum", "rating": 6, "date": "2026-02-23", "title": null, "content": "Jason Statham plays a retired (special forces/assassin/army ranger/etc) who is trying to live a peaceful life until some bad people threaten his (family/friend/pet dog), forcing him out of retirement and he has to fight his way to the head bad guy/girl, leaving a trail of bodies in his wake.\n\nThis is the template for most of Jason Statham's movies, recycled from the direct-to-DVD eras of Dolph Lundgren, Jean-Claude Van Damme, etc.\n\nBut Jason has two distinct things going for him: 1. He is 20 years younger than his predecessors, leaving him pretty much the only current action hero on the block (Dave Batista and Jason Momoa being the other contenders).\n\n2. The current state of cinema is so poor that a mediocre macho-action flick stands out as worth seeing.\n\nSo we have The Stath doing his stuff, which he does very well. It is all very watchable, all very predictable, all very implausible. The script is weak and leaves many loose ends, but who cares?\n\nBodhi Rae Breathnach does a fine job holding her own against him, ensuring that her character isn't just forgettable."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "f6dca09e-bdbc-4347-adfb-9e970e09f1d8", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:31.147978", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "6e20631b57f9adf2925b6b7caa01324fdbc092760afc936d42e80c7af183c00b"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "author": "TheFilmDetective", "rating": 7, "date": "2026-02-04", "title": null, "content": "Shelter starring Jason Statham is exactly the kind of gritty, no nonsense action thriller.\n\nStatham brings,his usual steely presence and physical intensity to the big screen making this character his own.\n\nThe film actually does a solid job at creating a bleak, rough around the edges atmosphere, Also sharp, tense, and satisfyingly brutal. That said, the movie doesn't take many risks,the plot feels familiar to some of his past movies he has done.\n\nWhile Statham tries to carry the movie with his charisma and toughness, Statham is ultimately stuck in this certain role that never challenges him to take on a different role.\n\nIt's just another typical Jason statham movie so overall Shelter was a serviceable, moderately entertaining movie.\n\nThis is unlikely that this movie will stand out more among his stronger or more memorable performances.\n\nBut It gets the job done.\n\nJust don't expect anything groundbreaking."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "1e0a6130-4d52-4e76-b040-5ae8427d20a9", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:31.147978", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "391ce5d63359254d46f40b79e4ff05376f45d93ca7e1bf4a321895c41422982f"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "author": "nigepitz", "rating": 7, "date": "2026-03-10", "title": null, "content": "So The Stathe's movies have become so formulaic of late that you could write the plots in advance using only a hundred words and come pretty close (Beekeeper, Working Man are the same film for example) Shelter follows the same formula but at least tries to balance the fighting (much less of this now he's getting old) with some moody reflection and hence it's far more enjoyable."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "fc642a46-f5c9-471b-936e-3e4be5f1aa3e", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:31.147978", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "ded8a4835f0b284756c26e0f73a410a92e00d4d6277a0e6a8467788c80d2504a"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "author": "Hammer-Rocks", "rating": 7, "date": "2026-03-06", "title": null, "content": "The plot revolves around survival, loyalty, and the cost of protecting the people you care about. It's simple but effective, and the emotional beats land because the film doesn't rush them. There's a sense of moral grey throughout. No one is spotless, and everyone is trying to outrun something.\n\nShelter isn't a blockbuster spectacle, it's a lean, character driven thriller that plays to Jason Statham's strengths while giving him more emotional depth than usual. It's the kind of movie that keeps you hooked from start to finish, not because it's loud, but because it's focused. If you enjoy Statham when he's both dangerous and vulnerable, this one hits the mark."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "e3611f05-7fa6-4b9c-a316-361be5f170e4", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:31.147978", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "e67dfd556e9098ef14cf979fff9355815296ea74b9e923ff1806436eeb57939a"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "author": "everitt-richard", "rating": 10, "date": "2026-03-02", "title": null, "content": "I might be a bit biased as Jason is one of my favourite actors but this is excellent. You like him and his previous films you will love this. Great actors as well as the young girl Bodhi he looks after in the film. Great action scenes. A lot of people call this a b movie but I don't agree. Great Scottish scenery and had me on the edge of Mt seat. Chance of a sequel?"}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "0a75711a-6f92-4cb5-8cb6-b69750744be7", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:31.147978", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "8f659f20e93ff2a959fbdc9cd9629a1ed3a073553ca7f4eecbcf7b6108de17fa"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "author": "southdavid", "rating": 6, "date": "2026-02-27", "title": null, "content": "I did not have much anticipation for \"Shelter\" having sat through \"A Working Man\" and \"The Beekeeper\" in the previous two years and found them to be tedious and forgettable action films. Imagine my surprise then when, halfway through the film I found myself thinking that this was actually alright.\n\nMichael Mason (Jason Statham) lives a life of isolation on a remote Scottish island. He only contact is with the man who brings him provisions once a month, and that mans daughter Jessie (Bodhi Rae Breathnach) who actually brings them ashore. When the ship bringing them sinks, Mason saves Jessie but has to go to the mainland to get medical supplies. There he's briefly caught on camera, which triggers a government squad to come to the island to attempt to take him in.\n\nSure, it sounds the same as always. In all three of those films, I've mentioned Statham is, or was, a trained assassin or elite soldier who has to reluctantly bring his skills out when someone comes for him, or someone he cares about. Whereas I found \"The Beekeeper\" to be unnecessarily quirky and \"A Working Man\" to be boring - \"Shelter\" finds the right tone and pace to be neither of the above. It's largely practical effects, which leaves us with the impression that Mason is genuinely just a well-trained solder, rather than a superhero.\n\nThis was my second film of the year for Breathnach and she's proved just as capable here as she was in \"Hamnet\". There are smaller supporting roles for Daniel Mays and Harriet Walter.\n\nIt doesn't get a better score because despite being lean and tight and practical it is still all very predictable stuff. But it's the best example of this predictable stuff that I've seen in a while."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "6c3f3288-64c3-4e01-8843-939c2466a8e9", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:31.147978", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "f70addcd0865028601c617be1eeba406827708bff7725f7e80a46cbda85ac0bf"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "author": "healingtoolbox", "rating": 8, "date": "2026-02-02", "title": null, "content": "Better than I expected! If you liked Jason's Jan 2024 Beekeeper, this is on the same level of quality. Seems to me film reviewers, both lay and pro, are not adapting to our cinematic times. There must be 1000 to 2000 action films similar to Jason Statham's Jan 2026 Shelter.\n\nSeems to me, reviewers score movies like this based on originality. This is an error. Modern action movies are always going to recycle the same tropes. Who disputes this? The better metric is COMMITMENT. If an actioner like Shelter has committed a directing and acting, it should get a higher score than an actioner just \"painting by the numbers.\"Shelter is made with commitment. It's directed with commitment. The actors are committed. The young girl is especially effective, an echo of the young Jennifer Lawrence here. She makes excellent use of her role and dialogue which are awfully familiar. Bill NIghy is effective in his supporting role. Shelter has one of the most effective soundtracks I've heard in a year or so, something like Tangerine Dream meets X-files (Michael Manring). Very appropriate and \"pluses\" plot points at every turn.\n\nCompare Shelter with the last few Aaron Eckhart actioners. I'm sad to say except for his first one or two actioners, Aaron's films have been more \"paint by number\" with little commitment to distinguish them."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "fbb4abaf-c202-4831-92d1-a5ad91cd8052", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:31.147978", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "4419dec221eba6ecf7a5923938095a615c231babdfbc801a2f223c39cc47aae4"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "author": "SpyroDungeon", "rating": 4, "date": "2026-02-21", "title": null, "content": "Jason Statham is back with a new film, although I'm not entirely sure if it's truly a new film. It's largely shaped by his fight scenes, many of which, while good, are repetitive and have similar consistency. Beyond that, the plot moves quickly. While the interesting scenes and conspiracy elements are quite appealing, the film doesn't quite offer anything truly new and features some rather uninteresting performances. The Manafort character was quite interesting, but I think he was wasted too quickly. He could have been developed further, and the film could have explored new action sequences, but it chose the easy way out. It's okay, predictable. If you want to watch another Jason Statham film, it's up to you."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "36bba954-b78c-4f70-aab9-b6c41cd4a741", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:31.147978", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "4e95b289dfe72bf140bdf9e4c13e751e2fc0f138b180dd922367e356a5780a7a"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "author": "That_one_kdrama_fanboy", "rating": 10, "date": "2026-02-25", "title": null, "content": "*Shelter (2026)* completely swept me away, and so much of that magic comes from Jason Statham. I'm used to seeing him as the unstoppable force, the man who walks through chaos without blinking but here, there's an added layer of depth that truly moved me. The intensity is still sharp as ever, yet there's a quiet vulnerability beneath it that makes his performance feel richer and more human. He doesn't just command the screen physically, he carries it emotionally. Every glance, every pause, every restrained reaction feels intentional and powerful.\n\nThen there's Bodhi Rae Breathnach, who is absolutely phenomenal. She doesn't just \"keep up\" with Statham, she stands beside him with such natural confidence and authenticity. Her performance feels raw in the best way, never forced, never overly polished. The emotional truth she brings to her role adds so much heart to the film. You can feel the sincerity in every scene she's in, and it genuinely touched me.\n\nWhat makes it even more special is the chemistry between them . Their dynamic feels organic and beautifully balanced. It's not about one overshadowing the other. It's about how their performances weave together, creating moments that feel honest and deeply affecting. The emotional scenes especially hit me hard, and I found myself completely invested in their journey.\n\nBy the time the ending arrived, I was overwhelmed in the best way possible. The emotions lingered long after the credits rolled. This film reminded me why I love cinema in the first place, because when performances are this heartfelt and sincere, they stay with you. *Shelter* isn't just about action or intensity. It's about connection, and both actors deliver that with incredible grace."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "5bdcf2d9-4f0d-4fb0-b839-2121bbb4fb8d", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:31.147978", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "0cdbf320a74557e2d43c997c562c778a82986e7a2ad38d7ef1cf17a0395f0a58"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "author": "bowmanblue", "rating": 6, "date": "2026-02-19", "title": null, "content": "Jason Statham plays, er, well, pretty much every character he's played in the last five years. A former - insert special forces unit - who's destined to get back into the fight to take on - insert whichever gang of bad guys need his brand of justice. Here, he's forced to leave a remote, windswept Scottish island to protect a young girl who's been washed up on his shores while confronting old enemies (including a solid supporting turn from Bill Nighy as a cold agency director).\n\nIt's a pretty average Jason Statham film. If you've seen one of his recent action movies, such as 'The Beekeeper,' or 'The Wrath of Man,' you've basically seen this one. The formula is comfortingly familiar: stoic Statham, minimal dialogue, efficient brutality, a reluctant protector role and enough explosions to keep things moving.\n\nThat said, it's not the worst in his catalog. The action sequences are well-choreographed and briskly paced, the remote island setting adds a moody, atmospheric backdrop and Statham himself remains reliably charismatic. He commits fully, even if the role doesn't demand anything new from him. The dynamic with the young co-star brings a bit of heart and the film clocks in at just about a reasonable runtime almost without overstaying its welcome.\n\nIf you're a die-hard Statham fan who just wants to see him dispatch bad guys with precision, this will suit you perfectly. But it's hardly a stand-out in his career - more of a solid, disposable popcorn flick that delivers exactly what you expect and little more."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "6a904c85-b7b3-4845-abab-71927ae6d4e6", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:31.147978", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "ae042c1dea7e821fdc30b0856ff4c34b3b6c34ae0e997979a54987edbb68a1e8"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "author": "firti", "rating": 2, "date": "2026-02-26", "title": null, "content": "I thought how bad it can be for a Thursday night. How wrong I was. They got lazy nowadays I am not sure if someone really wrote that script or they gave scripts of Jason Bourne & Leon to AI to mix & match. This is the worst of Statham's franchise. I hope they will not come up with a follow up movie named 'Jesse'"}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "2ccfe4c2-56d0-4e61-b091-d62d249597ea", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:31.147978", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "c04f29487aa035cd64d8b39828569cb029d278da1cb976779dd5a3d85d725d41"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "author": "JordanG-515", "rating": 10, "date": "2026-02-11", "title": null, "content": "Shelter is a gritty action-thriller that leans heavily into familiar territory for Jason Statham fans: a tough, taciturn lead with a troubled past, set against a backdrop of violence, survival, and unlikely bonds. Such underrated film and lots of thrilling action in the film. Would recommend it for sure."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "b746acbe-c0e2-4945-8351-8781835a6a4c", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:31.147978", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "9ddd34cf8278eedfa9522b5afc595b07e9337b76118e1fd9168d02d61d1d7141"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "author": "MorfenZ", "rating": 6, "date": "2026-02-06", "title": null, "content": "This movie feels like a mix of John Wick and Jason Bourne, borrowing a lot of familiar elements from both. At the center of it all is Jason Statham, and as always, he's untouchable and basically playing himself which is exactly what you expect. The overall cast is quite solid, and the fighting choreography and gunplay are well done. The action and direction are generally strong and carry the film most of the way. Story-wise, there's nothing new here, and the buildup is uneven. The first act starts very slow with too many question marks, the middle part also drags, and then the third act feels rushed in a weird way. The ending should have been the strongest part of the movie, but it isn't. Overall, this is a steady, standard Jason Statham one-time watch for me."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "74602303-86d6-4bc3-aaca-3e6ff4b59005", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:31.147978", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "89eb981704c35e9fe007e8dafdd6a2874e1ce38193d1197afb7505cc6faa66d5"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "author": "ColinTheGorilla", "rating": 5, "date": "2026-02-05", "title": null, "content": "So going into this movie I had some ideas of what would happen and the movie basically follows the simple Jason Statham action movie formula to a tea and doesn't add anything really new. First off the movie has some solid action scenes throughout the movie and they are choreographed really well for the most part but sometimes they are shot quite weird but for the most part they end up working and it's always fun to see Jason Statham just going around and killing people for the most part but this formula is getting dry and boring. Jason Statham gives an ok performance but he doesn't do a whole lot of anything new and continues to do the things you expect him to do. The writing in this film also isn't the greatest because for some reason the movie gives us barley any villains or any we should actually care about and they don't even bother to flesh any of them out to make them interesting. Also the movie introduces us early on to the character Jesse but it feels like her and Michael's relationship is really weird and they don't have the greatest chemistry together and it feels off at sometimes. The movie also has really bad pacing issues and the movie just continuously feels like it's dragging on for scenes and that some scenes felt stale and useless to the overall story. The dialogue is just really weird in this movie and messy with every single character in this movie and it gets weirder as the film continues. I think the first half of the movie really had something going to it and the film really starts off strong but the second and third act just lost me throughout the runtime of the film just leaving me disappointed and wanting more overall for the remainder of the movie. I do think though the cinematography is pretty good at times and they shoot the movie quite well besides for some weird shaky camera moments and how the film felt very grey in parts of the movie which made me feel even weirder about what was happening. This movie isn't bad but it ultimately fails and ended up leaving me disappointed unfortunately."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "95acb09e-c42a-4ff7-90f7-2704d0e36683", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:31.147978", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "02ae8199a15fe02a63268b051d57ed6d014f1ccff4eba4c9113edf2b7d7fb696"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "author": "georgeszaslavsky", "rating": 9, "date": "2026-01-31", "title": null, "content": "This movie suprised me on a lot of levels. The plot was interesting and the filming location too and this was also produced by Statham itself. The action scenes especially hand to hand combat and gun fighting scenes are spectacular. The conclusion of the movie is as one could predict but it is well done. I recommend this movie if you want to see something different from Jason Statham."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "8d51f800-6d4d-401e-995e-109972899626", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:31.147978", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "7a0a0db0763e87c0e8d8c3d7e041bdad224db12caa4622441e7cd1398c6086ba"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "author": "rgkarim", "rating": 6, "date": "2026-01-31", "title": null, "content": "LIKES: The Premise to A Point The Character Development The Camerawork The Filters The Sound Editing/Effects The Action Moments The Heart Summary: When I saw the limited ads for this movie, I had intended to think it was rescuing from human trafficking. This movie was not quite that, as the summary suggests, and was instead a film with a little more spy element to it than anything else. An interesting premise, if clich\u00e9, it works in Stratham's wheelhouse and offers the opportunity for a deeper plot than the usual elements we've gotten. To some degree, the gamble worked for me, with character development extending to a greater depth than the usual rough-and-tumble nature that this man excels in portraying. These moments have a lot of heart to them, and those touching moments help add some more layering that offers a reprieve from the onslaught of...walking, talking, and some action. There are several moments I found very engaging, and wanting a bit more focus and development in those moments than I had expected. And yet it's the action moments that were also my favorite. I'm a sucker for a good action film, and Statham's work is still somewhat impressive. There were a few moments that felt a pinch more unique flavor, blending the same lethal precision and creative measures he finds to eliminate his opponent. At these times, Statham's movie shines, especially when paired with a nice relevance and meaning to their inclusion.\n\nIn terms of development, the film achieves what I expect from these types of movies. It starts with the camerawork, and though I didn't find anything that blew my mind, I was also pleased to have stable work that gave me a lot of good details and little shake. You'll have a good idea of what is happening, with choreography and camera dancing to give us a performance easy to follow, and laughing with joy at the \"justice\" being dealt. I absolutely loved the filters and how they added some emotional vibes to the film. Though the grey filter tired me at times, it adds a lot of the feelings of the movie, and some of the other locations get a better vibe that I liked, but kudos to the lighting and filters to assist with engaging the film. And the sound effects only further give us that thrill as guns blaze, fists punch, cars break, and a multitude of other elements that always give more of those awesome action stunts I like. It's all rather familiar, but hey, there is nothing wrong with a little familiarity.\n\nDISLIKES: The Plot Is Contrived Committed One Of My Cardinal No-Nos Predictable The Story Is Thinner The Fighting Could Have Used A Bit More Unique Flavor Boring At Times Needed More Time More Of The Same Summary Regarding dislikes, the movie unfortunately falls into the same levels of this style of movie. I'll take a moment to say they did one of my supreme dislikes involving animals, and their poor utilization to just get an emotional response that is not fully etched out. Despite a movie with more layers, the film is a bit contrived in how all the action arises. What starts as a simple good deed coalesces into something much deeper, and while it could have been full of twists and clever executions, it was instead a hasty, convenient set of anomalies that just happen to align. It's the same predictable elements that come with his movies, a strong opening suddenly thinning out into subplots that may or may not become a spin-off (depending on whether Hollywood has its way). Those tangents ironically hold the most intriguing story elements, but when they are abruptly cut or tied off, it only makes for a boring distraction to add time to the movie. Again, time is precious, and attention spans are shrinking for them to engage in, but perhaps helping to trim back so many characters and side stories could have achieved something more. And perhaps some of that sacrifice could have led to more action scenes as well, because though it did have some awesome moments, the action overall felt a little tempered down. Many scenes have lost that Statham edge, realistically executing the moves, but losing some of the spice given all the circumstances. It dials back up in the end, but by that point, it's too rushed and late to capitalize on. So, for an action fan like me, I would have liked to see a little more. Overall, the movie needs more time to optimize everything, and try to break out of the familiar formula of these films that we get at least once a year.\n\nThe VERDICT: Shelter is a film that holds many familiar elements that are essential tools in this man's legacy. A story that holds some layering offers the contrived setting for the action, which, at times, is still one of the engaging and fun elements of the theater. The production quality is fine, with good camera technique and sound effects to capture the moments of fun, and it runs at a pace that should be fine for most attention spans. As such, the movie is still more of the same, a film that, despite the promise of something more, becomes another quick tangent that is familiar and perhaps a bit underwhelming. With a more contrived story, some lackluster character development, and toned-down action moments for much of the film. Shelter feels like a stream at home movie when it arrives in a few weeks. My scores for the film are: Action/Thriller: 6.5 Movie Overall: 6.0."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "8dd7dddd-fb1a-49b2-b0a6-4193595e9ad9", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:31.147978", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "411cfda2bbb96625aa1ce63f908af42ffd7b12f0b544dfee8d0a6aa4268a1393"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "author": "Shaydsi", "rating": 2, "date": "2026-02-05", "title": null, "content": "I enjoy Jason Statham films, they're easy watching action flicks that are entertaining despite pretty much all of them have him doing the same thing.\n\nThis wasn't, the first 45 minutes is almost unwatchable. Apart from the boat capsizing scene, nothing happens. I understand they're trying to build a relationship between Stathams character and the girl but it doesn't do that very well, I mean no disrespect to the young girl but her acting is poor and that is partly what made the first act of the film very difficult to stay interested in.\n\nThe action/fight scenes are exactly what you'd expect from a Statham film, well choreographed and engaging but there's not many 'bad guys' for him to fight in this movie. Bill Nighy does a less than stellar job with his role as the main bad guy behind a computer, and is killed after a 10 second dialogue with Statham at the end. Nighy's on call assassin is really the only person Statham fights in the movie, he has no lines and isn't for one second someone you think may cause Stathams character any problems at all.\n\nAll in all a pretty poor movie and not one i'd recommend spending money on going to watch. Just wait for it to come out on Netflix and even then I wouldn't add it to my watchlist..."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "e62a7f22-1061-4a4d-b43d-90f3811b1f1c", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:31.147978", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "3ae34cdfb0854a8f7bba6e57a0c34ec80e212c96ad089ffbd6fc9490f86b3e0b"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "author": "destroyerwod", "rating": 7, "date": "2026-02-25", "title": null, "content": "Did you enjoyed The Beekeeper and A Working man? If yes you should enjoy this one. Its Jason Statham doing Jason Statham things.\n\nWhile there may be a little less action than the 2 movies mentioned above, what is in really is what you want in a Statham movie.\n\nThe chemistry with the teen actress was also there, and while the plot is very typical for movies like this, it serves its purpose.\n\nThe antagonist tough really had the charisma of a broom, but i think it is at least half on purpose, as he is suppose to be a cold killer with no conscience. That said while the fights were fun, his lack of aura/charisma did hurt a little bit, but not enough to not enjoy the fights.\n\nOverall its a solid fun action movie. Its the kind of movie i enjoy seeing Jason Statham make."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "31c54c9e-a51f-490c-9e88-0b42cc94ced0", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:31.147978", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "f6ff25f798fe814b6021e4dd3db65994845a6cf5875c4c735b54c6723996e792"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "author": "Jeremy_Urquhart", "rating": 5, "date": "2026-02-11", "title": null, "content": "I think Jason Statham is contractually obliged to star in an action/thriller film every January. His 2026 one is Shelter. It's Leon the Professional, John Wick, and some dreary spy stuff thrown into a blender. The spy side of things is somehow the most boring and entertaining part of the movie. It's always sluggish when it focuses on that side of things, but the movie is so exhausted any time it has to deal with spy stuff that it's kind of funny. You can feel the movie sighing, heaving, and rushing its way through these parts, and that's sometimes unintentionally funny, and sometimes crushingly tedious.\n\nShelter also has an agonizingly slow start. I feel like there's some competent action once it gets going, especially in the second half, but nothing more than pretty decent. I don't think merely okay action really saves the movie or makes it worth watching, but there's some punchy-punching, cars going crashy-crash, and the apparently obligatory night club set piece that felt obligatory almost a decade ago now (I don't want to blame it all on John Wick, but he certainly didn't help).\n\nStatham is gruff and he is good enough at being gruff. Some of the lessons he passes off to the girl he's forced to protect are forced and eye-rolling, but thankfully infrequent. I think most people here knew what kind of movie they were in and didn't over-exert themselves. There's a level of \"eh, it's okay\" to much of it, so I can't call it terrible, but it's also a movie that's just there. I think the movie wants me to forget about it, like I was being Eternal Sunshine of the Spotless Mind-ed while it was still going."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "ba14d3b2-5195-40ee-8c31-e5c94fb81a01", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:31.147978", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "9bce433c527ac0dfa77a2dc38239ff5f4f9e9ddfef03eb984748be2adbe340c1"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "author": "danchilton-71955", "rating": 7, "date": "2026-02-22", "title": null, "content": "The start of another year means it's time for the annual \"Jason Statham is a retired killing machine trying to live a quiet life but being forced to start stacking obituaries\" movie. The typically nondescript title of this year's offering is Shelter and Stath's former special forces badass is called Michael Mason. When the British government agency that he used to drop bodies for comes calling at his remote Scottish lighthouse he is forced to take action, something that is complicated by the presence of a young orphan girl named Jessie (Bodhi Rae Breathnach). While our protagonist and his reluctant charge tear across the countryside, Naomi Ackie (criminally underused here) and Bill Nighy (putting in just enough effort to get by) scheme against each other at Spy HQ.\n\nJason Statham movies can essentially be judged on three criteria; Does he get to do cool action? Are the bad guys formidable enough? Is the plot and dialogue entertainingly cheesy rather than just eyerollingly bad? Shelter gets a pass on all three.\n\nAction wise, the scale isn't huge but we do get to see our leading man hit all the beats. There's some running around with a gun, a very solid car chase and, most prominently, a bunch of fisticuffs. The hand-to-hand stuff is more in your face than flashy, as is the style of director Ric Roman Waugh, and has a solid heft to it. The final throwdown in particular is bonecrunchingly satisfying and has an inventive finish.\n\nFor the action to hit home, Jason needs decent foes to go against. He may have a different name and (slightly different) backstory in each movie but it's hard not to think of every character he plays as roughly the same dude. Consequently, he needs adversaries that match up to his previous movies. One of the reasons last year's A Working Man was such a disappointment was that the low rent gangster foes felt like a comedown from the SWAT teams and kill squads our Cockney action man usually deals with. Fortunately we are back in the territory of government backed elite soldiers here, although not on the same scale as something like The Beekeeper. Particularly fun is Bryan Vigier as a killer agent billed as a twenty years younger version of Statham who pursues our heroes Terminator style throughout the film, leading to a handful of entertaining confrontations.\n\nDespite the movie's fairly grounded look, the plot doesn't let reality intrude too much on the action. This is the kind of film where you can nip down to London from the north of Scotland while your mate waits in the local boozer, and said boozer's wi-fi can be used to hack secure government servers. The over earnest dialogue also elicits a chuckle as Statham dispenses gruff wisdom to his young companion, such as how to hold a knife for stabbing efficiency and to never operate a gun from a \"place of fear\".\n\nSpeaking of fear, there is always the worry that a tag along child in an action movie will be annoying. There is one scene where she whines about being a bad person because she has watched Stath dispatch people like a postman delivering letters, but mostly she keeps her head down and handles things like a trooper. The way she takes everything in her stride is completely unrealistic, but in a film like this it's definitely the way to go.\n\nSo, with plenty of action, suitable punching bags, and a pleasingly dumb script, Shelter is a solid Statham flick. It doesn't exactly push the boundaries of action cinema, but an old-fashioned, light on the CG, mid-budget ass-kicker is always a pleasant distraction.\n\n7 Iranian defectors left alive out of 10."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "877983ad-d417-480d-a681-b2630cd0c0e2", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:31.147978", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "66136a4f9175759d358a1c3da8dad5f00fa8f2454f2b7dca9b9d42ef7f22296f"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "author": "Stardst1", "rating": 7, "date": "2026-02-26", "title": null, "content": "No matter his age,I think even when he's 100 or more, which I wish him with all my heart to reach,because he always gives us a gift that he is a thrill ride every time you watch him act it is his style and his style only and nobody can copy him or imitate him. I think I like the beekeeper more but again here he delivers with an action packed movie and a little bit of emotion."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "884ced5e-46dd-48e0-b3fa-e56a015404b2", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:31.147978", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "a2f7b47e49fe1c7728dfffb70cd12fb94d6b5b7ef0aa2381d81d44dd0c485913"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "author": "mazen-86", "rating": 9, "date": "2026-02-16", "title": null, "content": "I loved the movie it's light and fun lifts your spirits, and is perfect for watching on the weekend after the stresses of studying and work Jason Statham as usual is brilliant in this enjoyable film I wished the ending had been stronger but it was light and logical and I'm glad Jesse survived in the end."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "b76b3105-b029-40a9-b6c9-33a7bc3a7e00", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:31.147978", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "709b55d7a721ec242644cd670dec4f1a0f7ce05baa3045c97bc5fc7dfda1c801"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "author": "Miguel1226", "rating": 7, "date": "2026-02-08", "title": null, "content": "Shelter is a solid, well-made action thriller that delivers exactly what you'd expect from a Jason Statham-led film.\n\nThe story is straightforward and doesn't take many risks, but it's functional and keeps the movie on track. The real strengths are the action and visuals - set pieces are easy to follow, impactful, and feel properly staged rather than over-edited. The pacing is steady, with only minor slowdowns in the middle.\n\nCharacters are serviceable, with Statham's presence doing most of the heavy lifting. It may not be memorable in the long run, but it's an entertaining and rewatchable action movie."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "76d827a5-4df1-4c02-b0a7-3da1d47a3783", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:31.147978", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "c1bacc5718e062855f3e7744d53d74f8217fa3dd68d914e57e8ebbb3293520c4"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "author": "RegalsReelView", "rating": 5, "date": "2026-02-16", "title": null, "content": "A mysterious island hermit is forced to return to society to save a young girl. His return triggers a series of events that force him to confront his past.\n\nJust another Jason Statham action flick, but set in Scotland. A simple damsel-in-distress story arc with a slight twist. Some backstory is given to the characters and the plot, but not enough to make it interesting, exciting, or unique. There is not as much action and more quiet dialogue than would be expected. The one hour and forty-seven minute runtime is excessive for the substance of the movie. Not really worth the time, but fans can put it on in the background."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "e1c0c6bc-76a8-4251-8f0b-f163e85b2144", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:31.147978", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "9c1ca9ca028f7306385017a1541d24d95b448e544516965e32a030cc832a82ff"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "author": "liebercurtis", "rating": 8, "date": "2026-01-31", "title": null, "content": "I just watched this movie yesterday, Let me tell you, I really enjoyed probably every movie of Jason Statham.\n\nStatham never disappoints.\n\nYou can't go wrong with Statham.\n\nIt was little slow at first but the movie picks up.\n\nI always look forward seeing Statham's movies.\n\nThis movie has a lot of action and I thought just another great story, and another great job by Statham, and the entire crew.\n\nI would like to see more action but I still liked the movie a lot."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "13741d10-7eb1-40fa-8cea-95fde57cbb66", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:31.147978", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "ca6106d6b73aa86bba58a0a9b01b5a75eec3073ffe34f76b3ccff8a975b7726d"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "author": "linda-glass", "rating": 5, "date": "2026-02-06", "title": null, "content": "Unless you love action films this film is fairly boring. The premise and idea is good but the execution is too slow and this gets annoying. Love Jason Statham, he's an incredibly talented actor, I loved The Beekeeper but this just falls short. 5 stars for acting! The young girl is amazing in this. If you like action films you could enjoy this one, but I would wait till it goes on streaming. Have a great day!"}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "bb9d7ac0-70c2-4ead-b646-462901a43399", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:31.147978", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "c35aa5e35767c04d89e95b83fd090488e8de896b086246a74992427a8d0b500f"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "author": "schowdhuri-96566", "rating": 10, "date": "2026-02-02", "title": null, "content": "Jasaon Statham is back with another action packed film. It was a great cinematic experience and a great movie. Really enjoyed the visual effects and statham's action stunts. It starts with a dark, interesting story that suddenly turns into an action thriller. Great cast. It is better than previous movie beehive. Truly enjoyed as an audience."}}
{"metadata": {"ingestion_id": "74e452f5-c2ba-473b-906f-c515dad76fa8", "source_system": "imdb", "entity": "reviews", "extraction_method": "Scraping", "ingestion_timestamp": "2026-03-12T00:07:31.147978", "http_status": 200, "search_parameters": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "count": 100}, "raw_hash": "3af68743bff818df9797bafa539bf4f48fa5f4774171f417c6cf08ee453f3409"}, "raw_payload": {"movie_id": "tt32357218", "author": "edwalgomz", "rating": 9, "date": "2026-02-06", "title": null, "content": "Shelter hits the exact formula for a great action movie. The setup is classic: a reclusive former government agent who wants nothing more than to be left alone, his violent past buried for good. Of course, life has other plans. Circumstances pull him back into the world he's trying to escape, and because he possesses a very specific and dangerous skill set, he ultimately chooses to re-enter the fight for a noble purpose-protecting a young girl who has been tragically orphaned.\n\nThe young girl is portrayed by a talented and strikingly effective young actress who communicates far more through her quiet innocence and presence than through exposition or heavy dialogue. Her vulnerability feels real and unforced, and that fragility contrasts perfectly with the main character's restrained strength, wisdom, and barely contained brutality. The audience never doubts that she is in danger-but at the same time, there's a reassuring certainty that there are no safer hands in the world than those of Statham's character.\n\nWhat makes Shelter work so well is that it understands its formula and doesn't try to overthink or reinvent it. The film delivers plenty of government hitmen and shadowy agents, balanced by a sophisticated surveillance and monitoring apparatus that helps track movements and drive the plot forward. This structure gives the audience clarity without sacrificing tension, always letting us feel one step ahead while still anticipating the inevitable collisions.\n\nThe movie feels like a successful blend of familiar and beloved action archetypes-echoing The Professional and The Bourne Identity.\n\nOverall, Shelter is a strong, satisfying action film with a solid plot, emotional grounding, and well-earned violence. It functions on every level it sets out to-and for this particular brand of action storytelling, it's exactly what it should be."}}
